1
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:11,445
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:20,954
THE VILLAGE BARBER

3
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:26,026
BEYOND A MOUNTAIN
THAT RISES LIKE A WALL

4
00:00:28,328 --> 00:00:31,832
ACROSS THE ONLY BRIDGE STANDING

5
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:37,204
AND THROUGH A STRETCH
OF HOMEY ALLEYWAYS

6
00:00:39,239 --> 00:00:42,910
LIES A REMOTE RURAL VILLAGE
WITHOUT A SINGLE SUPERMARKET IN SIGHT

7
00:00:46,513 --> 00:00:52,853
THE VILLAGE BARBER
CUTS AND BLOW-DRIES

8
00:01:18,211 --> 00:01:20,113
- Thank you.
- Here.

9
00:01:21,014 --> 00:01:23,684
PARK BO GUM
OWNER OF THE VILLAGE BARBER

10
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:26,420
BARBER PARK BO GUM

11
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,622
WHAT MADE YOU DECIDE
TO OPEN THE VILLAGE BARBER?

12
00:01:28,689 --> 00:01:32,092
After obtaining my barber's license
during my mandatory military service

13
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:33,794
I've always thought

14
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:36,897
it would be nice
to do volunteer work with this.

15
00:01:36,964 --> 00:01:41,335
I'd been working on myself,
hoping to improve my skills

16
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:44,404
but word got out
even before I knew it.

17
00:01:44,471 --> 00:01:45,973
NATIONAL TECHNICAL
QUALIFICATION CERTIFICATE

18
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:47,908
LICENSE TITLE: BARBER
NAME: PARK BO GUM

19
00:01:47,975 --> 00:01:50,611
I often had hairstylists do my hair

20
00:01:50,677 --> 00:01:52,546
so I picked up a sense
of what looked good

21
00:01:52,613 --> 00:01:55,415
and at times, I'd even think,
"I might look better this way."

22
00:01:55,482 --> 00:01:57,050
So I started learning things
here and there.

23
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,920
I could see myself
becoming a hairstylist

24
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:04,658
if I no longer worked
as an actor in the future.

25
00:02:04,725 --> 00:02:08,128
I had hoped for a chance to start
a new chapter in life through it.

26
00:02:08,195 --> 00:02:10,163
And that anticipation

27
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:12,366
has become a reality faster
than I thought, thanks to this show.

28
00:02:12,432 --> 00:02:14,368
It must've been a year ago.

29
00:02:14,434 --> 00:02:15,669
DECEMBER 2024

30
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:17,170
THE VILLAGE BARBER:
CONFIRMED FOR ITS GRAND OPENING

31
00:02:17,437 --> 00:02:18,805
FEBRUARY 2025

32
00:02:18,872 --> 00:02:20,741
THE VILLAGE BARBER:
THE FIRST MEETING

33
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:22,042
APRIL 2025

34
00:02:22,442 --> 00:02:24,478
THE VILLAGE BARBER:
THE SECOND MEETING

35
00:02:24,544 --> 00:02:25,545
JUNE 2025

36
00:02:26,046 --> 00:02:29,149
D-200 UNTIL THE GRAND OPENING

37
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:32,319
JUST AS WINTER BEGAN TO FADE
AND HEAT BEGAN TO KICK IN

38
00:02:32,386 --> 00:02:34,321
- How have you been, everyone?
- Hello.

39
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:35,489
Hello.

40
00:02:35,555 --> 00:02:36,757
Have you been well?

41
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:39,259
So the actual shoot begins today.

42
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:40,327
BO GUM AND THE CREW'S THIRD MEETING

43
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:43,597
THE TABLET HE ALWAYS BRINGS WITH HIM

44
00:02:43,664 --> 00:02:47,367
We've had many discussions
starting last winter, haven't we?

45
00:02:47,434 --> 00:02:51,438
Basically, we're opening
a barbershop.

46
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:53,774
The biggest thing
that has been on my mind

47
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,977
is a location
which is far from hair salons

48
00:02:57,044 --> 00:02:58,745
to explain why I would choose
a particular village.

49
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:02,249
This area does not have
a hair salon or a barbershop

50
00:03:02,315 --> 00:03:03,784
and they don't even get
food deliveries.

51
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,887
There must be many other villages

52
00:03:06,953 --> 00:03:09,322
- Many of them.
- just like this one.

53
00:03:09,389 --> 00:03:11,224
I also want that space

54
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:13,460
to remain that way
after we settle there.

55
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:16,196
I'd love for it to remain like a set
where people can come in

56
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:19,032
for a cut or a blow-dry,
and even take photos.

57
00:03:19,099 --> 00:03:21,968
I want to add a touch of magic
to someone's life

58
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:25,372
so I hope this would become
a series of such moments.

59
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:27,641
That's been my biggest concern.

60
00:03:27,841 --> 00:03:28,842
I'm good at shaving off heads.

61
00:03:28,909 --> 00:03:29,910
WHICH HAIRSTYLE DO YOU DO BEST?

62
00:03:30,744 --> 00:03:31,745
A FORMER BARBER FOR HIS TROOP

63
00:03:31,812 --> 00:03:33,847
I did that for my troop
when I was in the Navy.

64
00:03:33,914 --> 00:03:37,417
Also, I know I'm good
at blow-drying and styling.

65
00:03:37,484 --> 00:03:39,586
- Perms too.
- Perms?

66
00:03:39,653 --> 00:03:41,421
I've never done it.

67
00:03:42,122 --> 00:03:45,625
You must get licensed
as a hairdresser to do perms.

68
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:47,060
- I see. Is that so?
- Yes.

69
00:03:47,127 --> 00:03:49,896
You aren't allowed to do perms
at a barbershop.

70
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:51,465
HE NEEDS ANOTHER LICENSE TO DO PERMS

71
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:52,532
LET'S STOP FOR A MOMENT

72
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:55,335
WHAT CAN YOU DO
WITH A BARBER LICENSE?

73
00:03:55,402 --> 00:04:01,742
SHAMPOO, BLOW-DRY,
WOMEN AND MEN'S CUTS, DYEING

74
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:06,613
SHAVING, DEEP-CONDITIONING, AND MORE

75
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:12,753
HOWEVER, YOU MUST OBTAIN
A HAIRDRESSER LICENSE TO DO PERMS

76
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:13,954
Are there three tests a month?

77
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:15,388
- Two.
- Two.

78
00:04:15,455 --> 00:04:16,890
WILL HE TRY TO GET LICENSED
TO DO PERMS?

79
00:04:16,957 --> 00:04:21,495
IT'S A TOUGH LICENSE TO OBTAIN
WITH A PASS RATE OF 20 TO 30 PERCENT

80
00:04:22,496 --> 00:04:26,566
ALSO, HIS SCHEDULE IS FILLED UP
UNTIL THE END OF THE YEAR

81
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,802
WILL HE OBTAIN THE LICENSE
IN THIS SITUATION?

82
00:04:28,869 --> 00:04:29,903
Well, if I'm going to do it

83
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:33,340
I want to be thoroughly prepared
before I begin.

84
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:35,642
I'll have to hurry, though.

85
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,077
I'll pass. I know I'll do well.

86
00:04:37,144 --> 00:04:38,578
I think you will.

87
00:04:38,645 --> 00:04:40,247
You'll probably aim
to get full marks.

88
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:42,115
I really want to.

89
00:04:42,182 --> 00:04:43,884
IT'S TRUE

90
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,353
BO GUM IS SERIOUSLY STUDYING
TO GET LICENSED JUST TO DO PERMS

91
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:50,724
DESPITE HIS BUSY SCHEDULE

92
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,359
AND SO, HE DOES NOT STOP PRACTICING

93
00:04:52,425 --> 00:04:53,727
When you see a nice glow...

94
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:57,597
EVEN DURING HIS OVERSEAS SCHEDULE,
HE STILL PRACTICES IN THE GREEN ROOM.

95
00:04:58,265 --> 00:04:59,266
Hello.

96
00:04:59,566 --> 00:05:02,869
HE HAD ONE DAY OFF IN A MONTH,
AND HE SPENT IT PRACTICING

97
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:07,240
HE EVEN COMES IN AT DAWN TO PRACTICE
AFTER A FULL DAY OF WORK

98
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:13,113
EVEN PARK BO GUM WORKS THIS HARD

99
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,081
Now, copy what I do.
Hang this on your thumb.

100
00:05:15,582 --> 00:05:18,318
Is it on your thumb?
Now, turn your hand into a gun shape.

101
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:20,220
Then, put the two fingers
into the rubber band.

102
00:05:20,287 --> 00:05:21,421
GAUNT

103
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:22,689
After that, lift them back up.

104
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:27,027
- First, rubber band on the thumb.
- On the thumb.

105
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:28,695
Then open to make two loops.

106
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,431
Did you get it?

107
00:05:31,798 --> 00:05:33,033
Did you make two loops? No?

108
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,768
Put both fingers inside.

109
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:36,069
Both fingers in here.

110
00:05:36,803 --> 00:05:38,071
And open. Okay.

111
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:40,006
Try doing that yourself.

112
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:43,076
SO HARD

113
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:45,579
Index finger first.

114
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,783
One finger at a time, and then
open both fingers at the same time.

115
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:50,951
Yes.

116
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:52,752
- Try practicing by yourself.
- Okay.

117
00:05:58,558 --> 00:06:01,528
STEP 2:
WRAPPING THE HAIR WITH PERM RODS

118
00:06:01,595 --> 00:06:02,596
And...

119
00:06:04,598 --> 00:06:06,333
Good job.
Hold tightly to the tip of the hair.

120
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:07,934
Do not even let go of one strand.

121
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:09,002
Do you understand?

122
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:11,805
Now fold this part down.

123
00:06:12,906 --> 00:06:14,541
Roll it slightly and let it loose.

124
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:18,345
Yes. Wait, roll it this way here.

125
00:06:18,411 --> 00:06:19,446
A TOUGH DAY WITH THE ROD

126
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:21,681
No, don't let your hand go.

127
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:23,717
- Something like that.
- This is so hard.

128
00:06:24,584 --> 00:06:26,486
- What am I going to do?
- The tip of the hair is too...

129
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:28,021
RAGE

130
00:06:28,588 --> 00:06:29,689
This is so hard.

131
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:30,824
LOSING HIS MIND

132
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,626
- Down here at the bottom.
- What am I going to do?

133
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:34,828
No, it's okay.

134
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:39,399
FROM THAT DAY FORWARD,
THE CYCLE OF ENDLESS PRACTICE BEGAN

135
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:44,004
SPEED AND ACCURACY IS EVERYTHING
WHEN WRAPPING THE ROD FOR THE TEST

136
00:06:44,938 --> 00:06:45,939
HE SLOWLY BECAME AN EXPERT

137
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:48,208
Do not miss a strand.
Roll it once, then use both hands.

138
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:52,178
HIS HANDS HAVE GROWN STEADY NOW

139
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:54,748
Do not let it go.
One more roll. That's it.

140
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:01,855
THE RODS WERE CROOKED

141
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:04,024
SHOWING TOO MUCH PAPER

142
00:07:05,992 --> 00:07:07,093
RODS ARE LINED UP NEATLY

143
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,362
NOT TOO MUCH PAPER SHOWING

144
00:07:10,297 --> 00:07:11,364
I think I'm pretty good now.

145
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:16,269
AND AS HE CONTINUED
TO GROW MORE AND MORE CONFIDENT

146
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:17,337
Maybe it was a first.

147
00:07:17,404 --> 00:07:19,439
I haven't felt that way
in such a long time.

148
00:07:19,506 --> 00:07:21,308
I have no idea how I passed.

149
00:07:21,374 --> 00:07:23,310
PASSED?

150
00:07:23,376 --> 00:07:24,377
CONGRATULATIONS

151
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,947
HE PASSED THE WRITTEN TEST
FOR THE HAIRDRESSER LICENSE!

152
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,782
There were a few questions
I wasn't sure of

153
00:07:28,848 --> 00:07:30,383
while a lot of them were familiar.

154
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:33,086
The last question went,
"What is this haircut?"

155
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:38,258
It was tying up the hair like this
and cutting off the upper portion.

156
00:07:38,892 --> 00:07:42,095
But I'm so worried
about the practical test.

157
00:07:42,729 --> 00:07:43,730
NERVOUS ABOUT THE PRACTICAL TEST

158
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:44,798
The practical test.

159
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:48,735
HE HAS NO TIME TO BE ANXIOUS

160
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:52,005
HE'S NOW BUSY GETTING READY
FOR THE PRACTICAL TEST

161
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:57,811
IT MAY BE A NEW CHALLENGE

162
00:07:58,511 --> 00:08:00,547
LAYERED CUT:
VISUALIZING THE HAIRSTYLE

163
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:02,916
Numbers one, two,
three, four, and five.

164
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:05,051
Take a look at the supplies.

165
00:08:05,685 --> 00:08:07,921
AND SO, HE CONTINUED TO PRACTICE
ALL THROUGHOUT SUMMER

166
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:10,724
AND PRACTICED SOME MORE

167
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,627
JUST AS THE HEAT BEGAN TO DIE DOWN

168
00:08:14,694 --> 00:08:20,000
SEPTEMBER 2025
D-95 UNTIL THE GRAND OPENING

169
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:25,472
A SMALL HAIR SALON
AT THE CORNER OF A QUIET ALLEYWAY

170
00:08:28,575 --> 00:08:29,576
PARK BO GUM
THE OWNER OF THE VILLAGE BARBER

171
00:08:29,642 --> 00:08:33,013
Hi, it's nice to meet you.

172
00:08:33,546 --> 00:08:35,281
This is my first time filming
something like this

173
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:36,549
so I don't know what to do.

174
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:37,917
But I look forward
to working with you.

175
00:08:37,984 --> 00:08:39,819
LAUGHING

176
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:44,724
So, this is a hair salon that people

177
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:46,793
- in the neighborhood use.
- Yes.

178
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,128
Then, these prices feel

179
00:08:48,661 --> 00:08:53,433
more familiar to the elderly, right?

180
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,402
JINGLE

181
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,837
OPENING

182
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:00,507
Is it an actual customer?

183
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,209
EYES OPEN WIDE

184
00:09:04,511 --> 00:09:06,913
AT THAT MOMENT, A CUSTOMER WALKS
INTO THE HAIR SALON

185
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:07,981
You can't go in.

186
00:09:08,815 --> 00:09:11,217
- Why not?
- I'm sorry.

187
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:12,719
- I'm sorry.
- But I'm on the show.

188
00:09:12,786 --> 00:09:14,054
Can I go in?

189
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:18,758
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

190
00:09:19,926 --> 00:09:24,464
HE NEVER EXPECTED
TO BE REJECTED AT THE DOOR

191
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,468
PEEKING

192
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:31,237
GLAD TO SEE HIM

193
00:09:32,705 --> 00:09:34,474
- Hola.
- Hola.

194
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:35,542
LEE SANG-YI
BO GUM'S FAVORITE BIG BRO

195
00:09:35,608 --> 00:09:36,609
Have you been well?

196
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,578
You look great.

197
00:09:38,645 --> 00:09:40,547
- When did you arrive?
- I just got here.

198
00:09:40,613 --> 00:09:41,748
You know

199
00:09:41,815 --> 00:09:45,718
I tried to open the door,
but someone said, "You can't go in."

200
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:51,324
I said, "But I'm on the show,"
and they made me open the door again.

201
00:09:51,391 --> 00:09:54,094
I guess they weren't told
about how I'd dress.

202
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:57,230
He thought I was a regular customer.

203
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,735
- Hello.
- Hi, it's a pleasure to meet you.

204
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:03,837
KWAK DONG-YEON
BO GUM'S FAVORITE LITTLE BRO

205
00:10:03,903 --> 00:10:06,973
- Finally. Hello, Kwak.
- We finally meet.

206
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,575
- Kwak, take a seat.
- I'm Kwak. Hi.

207
00:10:08,641 --> 00:10:10,176
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- You're the real Kwak.

208
00:10:10,243 --> 00:10:11,544
Yes, I'm Kwak.

209
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,513
- May I address you by name?
- No need to be formal.

210
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,315
- I'm Lee Sang-yi.
- Hello.

211
00:10:15,381 --> 00:10:16,916
Whether straight or flipped,
it's Lee Sang-yi every time.

212
00:10:17,884 --> 00:10:20,820
My nicknames are Tomato,
Kayak, Rotator, Noon, and Race car.

213
00:10:21,421 --> 00:10:22,422
Hey, Sang-yi.

214
00:10:22,489 --> 00:10:23,523
I carry a bit of poetic touch.

215
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:24,891
- That's incredible.
- Right?

216
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:30,597
I'm really glad
that I get to do this with these two.

217
00:10:30,663 --> 00:10:32,232
I'm so relieved.

218
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:34,734
What did you like about us?

219
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:37,103
First of all...

220
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,805
First off, Dong-yeon...

221
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,008
- is thoughtful.
- I'm good at noticing these.

222
00:10:42,075 --> 00:10:43,076
A COMBINATION OF KINDNESS
AND THOUGHTFULNESS

223
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:44,711
And Dong-yeon is...

224
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:46,746
GENUINELY LOOKING AFTER HIM

225
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:48,414
- You look great with your hair up.
- There's a long strand.

226
00:10:49,115 --> 00:10:50,917
- Here's a mirror.
- This is how they act.

227
00:10:51,618 --> 00:10:56,156
These two are
very considerate of others.

228
00:10:56,222 --> 00:10:58,625
Anyway, we'll be running
The Village Borber.

229
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,394
What a medieval way to call it.

230
00:11:01,461 --> 00:11:02,462
"Barber."

231
00:11:04,063 --> 00:11:06,833
- We're opening a hair salon.
- Right.

232
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,735
I think The Village Barber is
a great title.

233
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:09,802
Right?

234
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:11,671
Not only are we here as barbers
in this rural village, but it sounds

235
00:11:11,738 --> 00:11:13,006
- like "magic" and "curl in Korean.
- Yes.

236
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:14,541
Not only are we offering
a privilege to the village

237
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,576
but I also wanted to give
a magical time to the people as well.

238
00:11:16,643 --> 00:11:17,644
That was the meaning behind it?

239
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:18,978
- Did you come up with it?
- Yes.

240
00:11:19,045 --> 00:11:21,147
- You're seriously...
- You like it?

241
00:11:21,614 --> 00:11:23,082
- I love it. I just realized.
- Really?

242
00:11:23,483 --> 00:11:26,519
Our ultimate goal is to present them
with a magical experience.

243
00:11:26,586 --> 00:11:28,988
I wanted this time to be a present

244
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:33,159
- and a magical moment for everyone.
- All the moments.

245
00:11:35,228 --> 00:11:38,298
AND FROM HIS FINGERTIPS WILL COME

246
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:41,834
THOSE MAGICAL MOMENTS

247
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,404
Do you want to try this?

248
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:45,738
I think I did it right.

249
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:47,307
LEARNING WHAT IT MEANS TO SHARE

250
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,075
- Do you like sweet potatoes?
- Sweet potatoes!

251
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:51,211
- It sounds great.
- Both sweet potatoes and potatoes.

252
00:11:51,644 --> 00:11:52,645
A MOMENT TO WARM EACH OTHER'S DAY

253
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:54,247
- I love you.
- I love you.

254
00:11:54,747 --> 00:11:56,316
And you'll be in charge of what?

255
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,818
- Probably hair.
- Hair.

256
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:01,454
I actually got a barber's license
when I was in the military.

257
00:12:01,521 --> 00:12:03,590
- A barber? Isn't that about shaving?
- Yes.

258
00:12:03,656 --> 00:12:04,958
Shaving and...

259
00:12:05,024 --> 00:12:07,393
- So, you could open a barbershop?
- I could.

260
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:10,196
I wanted to take this chance
to get a hairdresser's license.

261
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:11,598
- You wanted to.
- I wanted to.

262
00:12:11,664 --> 00:12:12,966
So, I'm preparing for that.

263
00:12:13,866 --> 00:12:14,867
PULLING OUT

264
00:12:14,934 --> 00:12:16,569
I've been learning.

265
00:12:16,636 --> 00:12:18,838
- You're really...
- "Nail Technician."

266
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:19,906
STUDYING
FOR THE NAIL TECHNICIAN LICENSE

267
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:22,075
TRYING TO GRASP THE SITUATION

268
00:12:22,141 --> 00:12:23,376
With your large

269
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,478
and rough hands?

270
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:27,013
The brush is too small.

271
00:12:29,182 --> 00:12:30,750
You're actually studying for it?

272
00:12:30,817 --> 00:12:34,254
Yes, I take classes
for the practical and written exam.

273
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,990
But I thought I might forget
the stuff for the written exam.

274
00:12:37,056 --> 00:12:40,093
I've been using a different notebook.

275
00:12:40,159 --> 00:12:43,696
I haven't done much studying yet.

276
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:45,098
OPENING

277
00:12:45,164 --> 00:12:46,599
You did study a lot.

278
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:47,700
I only got through one page.

279
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:51,904
It's in a different notebook.

280
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:53,373
The written exam is so hard.

281
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:56,242
WHAT'S THE NATIONAL NAIL LICENSE EXAM
SANG-YI IS PREPARING FOR?

282
00:12:56,843 --> 00:13:01,114
1. MANICURE AND PEDICURE

283
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:03,216
2. GEL MANICURE

284
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:05,251
3. NAIL EXTENSIONS

285
00:13:05,318 --> 00:13:08,254
4. NAIL TIP REMOVALS

286
00:13:08,755 --> 00:13:11,157
AND OF COURSE,
IT'S NOT AN EASY PROCESS

287
00:13:11,224 --> 00:13:13,459
LAST SUMMMER

288
00:13:14,761 --> 00:13:16,596
HE HAS BEEN PRACTICING
WHENEVER HE HAD FREE TIME

289
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:18,698
This is hard.

290
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:22,735
THE FIRST TRY

291
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:24,604
MESSY EDGES

292
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:27,373
UNEVEN SURFACE

293
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,977
Gosh, this is hard.
Gel polish is tough.

294
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:33,880
THE REASON WHY COLORING NAILS
IS HARDER FOR HIM

295
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,482
You have huge hands.

296
00:13:39,252 --> 00:13:41,087
HIS HAND IS 20.5CM

297
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,256
MALE HAND SIZE CHART
VERY BIG: OVER 20CM

298
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:45,558
HIS HANDS ARE VERY BIG

299
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,026
So, the brush is too small for me.

300
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,395
It's driving me crazy!

301
00:13:50,463 --> 00:13:53,866
A DAINTY BRUSH
COMPARED TO HIS HUGE HANDS

302
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,569
IT'S NOT JUST THE BRUSH

303
00:13:56,636 --> 00:13:59,038
EVEN THE SPONGE IS TOO TINY

304
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:02,141
AND THE SCISSORS TOO

305
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:04,344
BUT THERE'S ONE THING
THAT KEEPS HIM MOTIVATED

306
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:06,012
Have you practiced a little?

307
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:07,080
On my mom.

308
00:14:07,413 --> 00:14:09,749
- And my mom loved it.
- Did she?

309
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:13,252
She's now 63 years old.

310
00:14:14,587 --> 00:14:17,090
So it was the fact that
her son was holding her hand.

311
00:14:17,623 --> 00:14:19,025
It wasn't about my skills.

312
00:14:19,459 --> 00:14:22,562
It felt like she loved
the fact that we got to share

313
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:24,964
some warmth through this experience.

314
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:27,734
I realized it would be like this

315
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,136
- with the elderly when we shoot.
- Yes, it'll be like that.

316
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:32,605
I had a feeling they would like this.

317
00:14:32,672 --> 00:14:34,440
- I had to do it in a hurry.
- It's okay.

318
00:14:34,741 --> 00:14:36,109
I'm not sure if it's pretty enough.

319
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:37,276
It is.

320
00:14:37,343 --> 00:14:38,611
- It is pretty.
- It is pretty.

321
00:14:38,678 --> 00:14:40,113
- Goodness.
- It's a treat

322
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:41,547
to have people like you
do this for us.

323
00:14:43,116 --> 00:14:44,484
SANG-YI WILL SHARE LOTS OF WARMTH

324
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,352
- You've got this.
- I've got this.

325
00:14:46,686 --> 00:14:49,122
How does the exam start
when you first arrive?

326
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:50,656
Is it the shampooing part?

327
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:55,428
- We begin by cleaning the cuticles.
- I see.

328
00:14:55,495 --> 00:14:56,863
THE OLDER BROS ARE
DISCUSSING THE NATIONAL TESTS

329
00:14:56,929 --> 00:15:00,166
But these days, not many hair salons
have nail stations.

330
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:01,868
- Most are gone.
- You're right.

331
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:03,536
Our line of work in nails...

332
00:15:03,603 --> 00:15:04,871
"Our line of work"?

333
00:15:06,439 --> 00:15:07,874
Are you switching industries?

334
00:15:09,642 --> 00:15:10,743
I must do my best.

335
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:13,579
I feel good
when my skills can be put to use.

336
00:15:13,646 --> 00:15:19,185
When you planned this show
with the crew and gave me a call

337
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:20,486
I wondered why you invited me.

338
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:23,589
What was your plan for me?

339
00:15:23,656 --> 00:15:24,824
You're the funny one.

340
00:15:24,891 --> 00:15:26,259
- Do you want me to be your henchman?
- Like a parrot.

341
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:27,326
No way.

342
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:28,795
- You might be like the parrot.
- No.

343
00:15:28,861 --> 00:15:30,029
A parrot?

344
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:31,597
- But Dong-yeon really is...
- Is that me?

345
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:33,065
It's not!

346
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:34,200
Is that actually a metaphor?

347
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:35,802
A METAPHOR FOR DONG-YEON

348
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:38,070
- What do you mean by that?
- Don't say that.

349
00:15:38,571 --> 00:15:40,807
- You play a huge role.
- I just thought...

350
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:43,743
Dong-yeon could be the owner.

351
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:46,179
You don't need to mind me that much.

352
00:15:46,245 --> 00:15:50,316
If I don't get a specific role,
I can leave after today.

353
00:15:50,383 --> 00:15:51,484
No.

354
00:15:51,551 --> 00:15:53,586
- No, it's just...
- What are you talking about?

355
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:55,488
- We desperately need you.
- No.

356
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:57,523
Seeing them does make me feel better.

357
00:15:59,392 --> 00:16:00,393
I mean it.

358
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:02,195
It's relaxing.

359
00:16:02,562 --> 00:16:04,130
- We really need you.
- That's true.

360
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:08,334
So anyway, when we go to hair salons,
they always give us snacks.

361
00:16:08,401 --> 00:16:09,769
- Right.
- Such as tea.

362
00:16:09,836 --> 00:16:13,339
- Seoul has lots of winter snacks.
- That's a great idea.

363
00:16:13,406 --> 00:16:14,774
so I thought we could share

364
00:16:14,841 --> 00:16:16,709
I thought that I could prepare snacks
to make it feel welcoming.

365
00:16:16,776 --> 00:16:18,478
- I like the sound of that.
- I'm for it.

366
00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:22,482
DONG-YEON ALREADY HAD A PLAN

367
00:16:23,282 --> 00:16:24,417
Hello.

368
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:25,585
Please excuse me.

369
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:29,555
The bun turns out nicely
when the batter is full to the brim.

370
00:16:29,622 --> 00:16:30,990
I understand.

371
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:34,026
HE CAME TO LEARN
HOW TO MAKE WINTER SNACKS

372
00:16:34,093 --> 00:16:35,461
FROM A FISH-SHAPED BUN EXPERT

373
00:16:35,528 --> 00:16:36,863
The red bean paste

374
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:40,666
seems lighter than usual,
so did you add something else to it?

375
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,002
I told you that I mixed in milk.

376
00:16:43,069 --> 00:16:44,070
- Milk.
- Yes, milk.

377
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:46,472
That's why these are delicious.

378
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:49,842
Do you use the usual batter?

379
00:16:49,909 --> 00:16:52,245
- Are you trying to warm these up?
- Yes.

380
00:16:52,311 --> 00:16:54,514
If it doesn't get toasted,
how many more minutes do I need?

381
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,015
PRYING FOR KNOW-HOWS
TO MAKE DELICIOUS BUNS

382
00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:01,254
They come off like this.

383
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:04,991
I'd make another batch here
while that one cooks.

384
00:17:05,625 --> 00:17:07,460
Does this look too thick?

385
00:17:07,927 --> 00:17:09,962
- It's undercooked.
- Undercooked?

386
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,297
No, leave these here.

387
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:12,999
THE TOP BATTER MUST REMAIN THIN!

388
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:19,305
CONTINUES TO PRACTICE MAKING THE BUNS

389
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:20,540
Why is that happening?

390
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:24,677
DONG-YEON WILL BE IN CHARGE
OF THE BARBERSHOP'S SNACKS

391
00:17:26,012 --> 00:17:27,213
- Dong-yeon.
- Yes?

392
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,981
People are swarming in.

393
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,416
I've never had
such delicious fish buns.

394
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:31,484
It's a first.

395
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:34,921
A fish-shaped bun.

396
00:17:34,987 --> 00:17:37,256
How did you learn to make these?

397
00:17:37,323 --> 00:17:39,191
May I have more, Uncle?

398
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:41,360
- Was it good? Okay.
- Yes.

399
00:17:41,427 --> 00:17:42,862
My business is thriving.

400
00:17:42,929 --> 00:17:44,096
STAY TUNED FOR HIS BUNS!

401
00:17:45,865 --> 00:17:47,967
- Where are we going?
- Yes, where are we going?

402
00:17:48,034 --> 00:17:49,402
I've been curious to find out.

403
00:17:49,468 --> 00:17:50,670
It's a picture.

404
00:17:51,037 --> 00:17:52,138
A PICTURE?

405
00:17:52,204 --> 00:17:54,607
- Where is this?
- It looks like...

406
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:56,042
In the mountains?

407
00:17:57,443 --> 00:17:58,511
Where is this place?

408
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:01,948
It looks like a basin.

409
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:03,549
Just like Daegu.

410
00:18:03,616 --> 00:18:05,851
- It's bowl-shaped.
- Surrounded by mountains.

411
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:07,486
Daegu?

412
00:18:08,054 --> 00:18:10,656
That's Muju in Jeollabuk-do.

413
00:18:10,723 --> 00:18:11,891
- Muju.
- Muju?

414
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:12,992
Muju?

415
00:18:13,059 --> 00:18:15,127
- Why does it sound familiar?
- It's pretty.

416
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:17,063
Is there a hair salon here?

417
00:18:17,129 --> 00:18:18,497
- No.
- Not at all?

418
00:18:18,564 --> 00:18:20,933
Not at all.
They must leave the village.

419
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,070
You need a car because
it takes forever for a bus to come.

420
00:18:24,136 --> 00:18:28,107
Also, it may be tougher
for the elderly to drive.

421
00:18:28,174 --> 00:18:30,676
We could cut their hair

422
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:33,245
give them perms,
do their nails, and cook food.

423
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:39,051
I just want to revitalize
that small village.

424
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:40,586
Twenty-four hours won't be enough.

425
00:18:40,653 --> 00:18:43,823
I don't think you can do all that.
Your eyes are already bloodshot.

426
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:45,992
You have bloodshot eyes.

427
00:18:46,525 --> 00:18:48,861
But if I'm with you two,
I can do anything.

428
00:18:48,928 --> 00:18:51,097
Do you regret starting
this barbershop?

429
00:18:51,197 --> 00:18:53,399
DO YOU REGRET STARTING
THIS HUGE PROJECT?

430
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:55,534
No, I don't regret it.

431
00:18:56,102 --> 00:18:57,803
I want to do a good job.

432
00:18:57,870 --> 00:19:00,506
I want to give them good haircuts.

433
00:19:01,574 --> 00:19:02,675
You're the master barber.

434
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,143
Master Park.

435
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,511
Okay.

436
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:07,580
We're all captains.

437
00:19:08,914 --> 00:19:10,282
- No.
- Why not?

438
00:19:12,351 --> 00:19:14,987
NOVEMBER 2025
D-50 UNTIL THE GRAND OPENING

439
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:18,724
RENOVATING AN OLD HOUSE
THAT WAS ABANDONED FOR 5 YEARS

440
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:21,861
A SPACE THAT THAT WILL REMAIN
FOR THE LOCAL VILLAGERS

441
00:19:22,561 --> 00:19:24,196
COME RAIN

442
00:19:24,263 --> 00:19:27,967
OR COME SNOW

443
00:19:28,034 --> 00:19:32,171
THIS PLACE IS GETTING READY
TO WELCOME CUSTOMERS

444
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:36,142
BO GUM CAME BY TO CHECK
ON THE CONSTRUCTION PROGRESS

445
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:39,979
Hello.

446
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:42,248
I came by

447
00:19:42,982 --> 00:19:45,284
to check on the progress.

448
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:47,019
I'm hoping this place will become

449
00:19:47,086 --> 00:19:50,623
a refresher, a recharger,
and a reception room for everyone

450
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:53,859
and will continue to be used
even after we leave.

451
00:19:53,926 --> 00:19:55,127
That's why I'm here.

452
00:19:55,761 --> 00:19:58,197
Is that the shampoo room?

453
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,633
There's a hose sticking out.

454
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,234
CHECKING THE AREA
WHERE HE'LL RECEIVE CUSTOMERS

455
00:20:02,902 --> 00:20:04,837
These must be the mirror stations.

456
00:20:06,472 --> 00:20:08,641
So, there will be
about two chairs here.

457
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:09,709
EXCITED

458
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:10,843
And this is

459
00:20:11,277 --> 00:20:14,647
where people can sit around,
eat together

460
00:20:15,481 --> 00:20:16,782
and chat with one another.

461
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:18,784
I'm already getting excited.

462
00:20:26,926 --> 00:20:28,394
The ladies are coming over.

463
00:20:28,461 --> 00:20:29,495
They must be curious.

464
00:20:29,795 --> 00:20:32,231
When the wind blows from there,
it slides into my place.

465
00:20:32,298 --> 00:20:34,300
When the wind blows from there,
it slides into my place.

466
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:37,603
Sorry?

467
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,573
Is that so? I'm sorry.

468
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:42,675
- What?
- Do you use Styrofoam?

469
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,043
- Styrofoam?
- Yes.

470
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:46,278
No, we aren't using Styrofoam.

471
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:48,981
Something tiny flew over? I'm sorry.

472
00:20:49,048 --> 00:20:51,250
- Let us clean it for you.
- Leave it.

473
00:20:51,317 --> 00:20:52,651
I thought you were using it.

474
00:20:52,952 --> 00:20:54,186
We're sorry.

475
00:20:55,521 --> 00:20:58,324
Goodness, it's nice
to have young men here.

476
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:00,926
- Hello.
- Hello.

477
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,229
STROLLING AWAY

478
00:21:03,295 --> 00:21:07,233
I think it's my first time
coming by for a preliminary check

479
00:21:07,299 --> 00:21:09,168
before I actually begin shooting.

480
00:21:09,235 --> 00:21:10,736
I'll prepare everything thoroughly.

481
00:21:11,303 --> 00:21:12,471
But first

482
00:21:13,139 --> 00:21:14,774
I must do well on the written test.

483
00:21:18,043 --> 00:21:20,246
DAY OF THE HAIRDRESSER LICENSE EXAM

484
00:21:23,482 --> 00:21:27,486
BO GUM PRACTICED
UNTIL DAWN THE DAY BEFORE

485
00:21:28,721 --> 00:21:30,556
EXHAUSTED

486
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:33,959
GOING CRAZY

487
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:35,861
You need to start getting ready.

488
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:37,196
What time is it?

489
00:21:37,263 --> 00:21:38,264
It's noon.

490
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:40,800
GASP!

491
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:46,639
LOSING HIS MIND AGAIN

492
00:21:50,676 --> 00:21:55,648
PULLS HIMSELF TOGETHER
AND CHECKS HIS SUPPLIES ONE LAST TIME

493
00:21:56,482 --> 00:21:57,883
Do you have your ID?

494
00:21:58,584 --> 00:21:59,585
Yes.

495
00:22:00,586 --> 00:22:01,587
Bye.

496
00:22:02,154 --> 00:22:03,322
I'll be back.

497
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:05,991
