00:33:59,604 --> 00:34:01,773
What do you think?
Is this enough for you to cook?

752
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,942
This is honestly too much for me.

753
00:34:04,009 --> 00:34:05,243
- Really?
- This quality is...

754
00:34:05,310 --> 00:34:06,511
- It's beautiful.
- It is.

755
00:34:06,578 --> 00:34:07,946
CAN'T TAKE HIS EYES OFF

756
00:34:08,013 --> 00:34:11,616
This may be a barbershop,
but we'll have a lot of chores to do.

757
00:34:11,683 --> 00:34:14,719
But why does a barbershop
have a full-on kitchen?

758
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:18,790
THE KITCHEN IS STILL UNFAMILIAR

759
00:34:18,857 --> 00:34:20,825
This is my first time here,
but it doesn't feel unfamiliar.

760
00:34:20,892 --> 00:34:22,360
JOSTLING TOGETHER WITH THE VILLAGERS

761
00:34:22,427 --> 00:34:24,262
Everything feels so familiar.

762
00:34:24,596 --> 00:34:26,531
It's as if I saw it yesterday.
It's so nice.

763
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:27,999
That's good.

764
00:34:29,467 --> 00:34:30,669
The water is running well.

765
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:33,738
The water runs so well! That's crazy.

766
00:34:34,606 --> 00:34:35,807
I'm starting to feel

767
00:34:36,641 --> 00:34:38,243
very passionate.

768
00:34:38,310 --> 00:34:39,477
HIS COOKING PASSION IS SOARING

769
00:34:41,313 --> 00:34:44,683
THANK YOU

770
00:34:45,684 --> 00:34:47,819
These need to be portioned out.
Give me a moment.

771
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:49,254
They look delicious.

772
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:56,962
HOMEMADE PRESERVES
MADE BY DONG-YEON

773
00:34:57,662 --> 00:34:59,831
JUMPING WITH GLEE

774
00:35:00,799 --> 00:35:02,767
Thank you, everyone. I'm so happy.

775
00:35:02,834 --> 00:35:04,669
CELEBRATING THE OPENING OF THE SHOP

776
00:35:04,736 --> 00:35:06,504
Let's have our own opening ceremony.

777
00:35:08,506 --> 00:35:10,108
What was it again?

778
00:35:10,175 --> 00:35:12,310
"Gumdongyi"?

779
00:35:12,377 --> 00:35:13,678
- Gumdongyi.
- It was Gumdongyi.

780
00:35:13,745 --> 00:35:15,213
- Gumdongyi.
- It was Gumdongyi.

781
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:18,450
"Gum" from BO GUM, "dong"
from Dong-yeon, "yi" from Sang-yi.

782
00:35:18,516 --> 00:35:19,951
- Gumdongyi.
- Gumdongyi.

783
00:35:20,018 --> 00:35:21,019
THEIR OWN TEAM NAME

784
00:35:22,387 --> 00:35:25,690
A CAKE BO GUM ORDERED AND BOUGHT
FOR THE GRAND OPENING

785
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:28,293
One, two, start.

786
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:33,765
- Happy opening day
- Happy opening day

787
00:35:33,832 --> 00:35:36,835
- To our beloved Gumdongyi
- To our beloved Gumdongyi

788
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,871
- Happy opening day
- Happy opening day

789
00:35:41,706 --> 00:35:44,175
A SIMPLE YET MEANINGFUL
OPENING CEREMONY

790
00:35:44,242 --> 00:35:45,276
To The Village Barber.

791
00:35:45,343 --> 00:35:47,579
- Let's go!
- Thanks, guys.

792
00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:50,248
- It's snowing.
- It is.

793
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:51,816
- What?
- It's a white Christmas.

794
00:35:53,385 --> 00:35:56,588
BIG, FLUFFY SNOW FALLS

795
00:35:56,655 --> 00:36:00,759
AS IF TO CELEBRATE THE OPENING

796
00:36:05,563 --> 00:36:06,798
Are they sprinkling it?

797
00:36:06,865 --> 00:36:08,833
- No, it's coming down from the sky.
- It's actual snow, right?

798
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:10,268
How can this be?

799
00:36:10,935 --> 00:36:12,637
But the sun was out until just now.

800
00:36:14,472 --> 00:36:15,507
It's truly magical.

801
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:16,808
- It's magical.
- Magical.

802
00:36:16,875 --> 00:36:18,510
- Has it begun?
- It has.

803
00:36:18,576 --> 00:36:19,577
THE VILLAGE BARBER
WHERE MAGIC COMES TO LIFE

804
00:36:19,644 --> 00:36:21,946
EVEN THE WEATHER FEELS MAGICAL

805
00:36:22,013 --> 00:36:25,016
THE START OF THE VILLAGE BARBER

806
00:36:25,784 --> 00:36:27,952
As we're making preparations

807
00:36:28,453 --> 00:36:31,523
do you want to know
how my hairdresser license exam went?

808
00:36:31,589 --> 00:36:33,191
Perms were really hard.

809
00:36:33,458 --> 00:36:35,226
- How was it?
- I found it so hard.

810
00:36:35,293 --> 00:36:36,728
I thought I'd be good at it

811
00:36:37,395 --> 00:36:39,731
but perms were way harder
than I expected.

812
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:42,901
And you have to do it
within the time limit.

813
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:44,602
- Yes, that's what's nerve-racking.
- Yes.

814
00:36:45,003 --> 00:36:46,771
Bottom line, I failed.

815
00:36:47,305 --> 00:36:48,606
Bottom line, I failed.

816
00:36:50,709 --> 00:36:51,710
EYES WANDERING

817
00:36:51,776 --> 00:36:53,244
I failed.

818
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:56,247
What's that look on your face?

819
00:36:56,681 --> 00:36:58,817
WELL, SPEAK FOR YOURSELF

820
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:00,118
On the day of the test...

821
00:37:00,185 --> 00:37:02,420
PRACTICAL EXAM DAY
FOR THE HAIRDRESSER LICENSE

822
00:37:02,487 --> 00:37:04,689
...it's basically a sprint
toward perms.

823
00:37:04,756 --> 00:37:07,058
So, perms are generally hard.

824
00:37:07,125 --> 00:37:10,328
I asked my stylist for advice,
and she said

825
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:11,996
"Avoid an unfinished job
at all costs."

826
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:13,465
- So, you have to complete it.
- Yes.

827
00:37:13,531 --> 00:37:14,833
You fail immediately.

828
00:37:14,899 --> 00:37:17,535
- Right there on the spot.
- So, never leave it unfinished.

829
00:37:17,602 --> 00:37:19,804
So, I was rolling like crazy

830
00:37:19,871 --> 00:37:21,639
but everyone next to me was
already done.

831
00:37:22,474 --> 00:37:23,875
TERRIFYING

832
00:37:23,942 --> 00:37:25,510
But I still had a whole section left.

833
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:28,580
I had one minute left,
so I just rolled them.

834
00:37:28,646 --> 00:37:31,316
You're supposed to roll
using rods by color.

835
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:34,552
The proctor shouted,
"Hands off," so I let go.

836
00:37:35,186 --> 00:37:38,256
But you need at least 55 rods
per head.

837
00:37:39,057 --> 00:37:40,191
They counted and said

838
00:37:40,692 --> 00:37:42,360
"It's 45."

839
00:37:42,427 --> 00:37:43,728
- Ten.
- You were lacking ten?

840
00:37:43,795 --> 00:37:45,530
- You needed ten more?
- I was short by ten.

841
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:46,831
Yes.

842
00:37:46,898 --> 00:37:50,535
They yelled, "Hands off"
and everyone turned their heads.

843
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:52,504
Everyone was staring at me.

844
00:37:53,805 --> 00:37:55,774
HE CAN FINALLY LAUGH ABOUT IT

845
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:57,876
They probably knew who I was.

846
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:01,412
EMBARRASSED

847
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:04,115
But you rolled them.

848
00:38:04,182 --> 00:38:06,951
You rolled everything else.
You only missed five here.

849
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:09,721
I was the only one
who didn't finish in time.

850
00:38:10,321 --> 00:38:12,056
"Poor BO GUM. You have to let go."

851
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:14,125
- "Get your hands off, please."
- I let go.

852
00:38:14,459 --> 00:38:15,794
- You worked hard.
- You worked hard.

853
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:16,995
- Thanks.
- You worked hard.

854
00:38:17,061 --> 00:38:18,496
- Great work.
- Thank you for that.

855
00:38:18,563 --> 00:38:20,365
I guess I wanted to hear that.

856
00:38:21,099 --> 00:38:23,001
It doesn't change the fact
that you're the boss.

857
00:38:25,236 --> 00:38:28,439
But this isn't your only chance.
Take it again.

858
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,675
You can always try again.

859
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:33,244
I was honestly disappointed.

860
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:34,479
THE REASON IT STILL STINGS

861
00:38:34,546 --> 00:38:36,848
I thought I'd pass. I wanted to pass.

862
00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:41,519
Well, yeah.

863
00:38:41,586 --> 00:38:44,289
Although I can't do a rod perm

864
00:38:44,355 --> 00:38:49,661
I'm confident I can do a blowout
that looks like a heated perm

865
00:38:49,727 --> 00:38:52,096
so I think that's still something
to be grateful for.

866
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,731
A barber license means

867
00:38:54,265 --> 00:39:00,305
I can do cuts, shaving, and dyeing.

868
00:39:00,371 --> 00:39:03,608
I'll run The Village Barber
in a fun way.

869
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:06,544
We talked about it,
and now we're here.

870
00:39:07,045 --> 00:39:09,581
Honestly, it still doesn't feel real.

871
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:12,884
I don't know
how we're going to greet people

872
00:39:12,951 --> 00:39:15,854
- Right.
- and how we'll run this shop.

873
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:18,723
- I can't imagine what will happen.
- Exactly.

874
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:21,092
I wonder how many people we'll meet.

875
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:23,428
They said there would be
a lot of elders around here

876
00:39:23,494 --> 00:39:25,063
but there could also be kids.

877
00:39:25,563 --> 00:39:28,533
Should we call it a soft opening?
What should we call it?

878
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:29,667
Let's call it a rehearsal.

879
00:39:29,734 --> 00:39:31,536
- Something like a practice.
- Yes.

880
00:39:31,603 --> 00:39:34,205
Let's run a simulation
from the beginning.

881
00:39:34,272 --> 00:39:35,306
Let's say a customer came in.

882
00:39:35,773 --> 00:39:38,109
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

883
00:39:38,176 --> 00:39:39,177
A CUSTOMER APPEARS

884
00:39:39,711 --> 00:39:41,946
WHAT DO WE DO FIRST?

885
00:39:42,013 --> 00:39:43,381
Should we say,
"This is The Village Barber"?

886
00:39:43,448 --> 00:39:44,616
Yes.

887
00:39:44,682 --> 00:39:46,684
People usually say,
"Hello, welcome to our shop."

888
00:39:46,751 --> 00:39:48,620
- Welcome to The Village Barber.
- Welcome to The Village Barber.

889
00:39:48,686 --> 00:39:49,787
THEY ALL FREEZE

890
00:39:49,854 --> 00:39:51,489
I'm here for a haircut.

891
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:54,158
- Oh, yes, please take a seat.
- Okay.

892
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,627
- We should seat them, right?
- Yes.

893
00:39:55,693 --> 00:39:57,095
I'll take your coat.

894
00:39:57,161 --> 00:39:59,063
- The coat.
- We have to take their coat.

895
00:39:59,130 --> 00:40:00,198
- The coat...
- Hang the coat.

896
00:40:00,265 --> 00:40:01,499
- Where do I hang it?
- Here.

897
00:40:01,566 --> 00:40:02,567
There's a hanger.

898
00:40:02,634 --> 00:40:04,235
Hang their jacket.

899
00:40:05,270 --> 00:40:07,105
Please lie down comfortably.

900
00:40:07,772 --> 00:40:10,174
NOW IT'S TIME FOR A SHAMPOO

901
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:11,676
- Does it feel okay?
- It feels nice.

902
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:13,411
Okay.

903
00:40:13,711 --> 00:40:16,414
FIRST STEP OF SHAMPOO:
COVER THE CUSTOMER'S EYES

904
00:40:17,181 --> 00:40:18,683
Just a second.

905
00:40:20,585 --> 00:40:21,819
What's this?

906
00:40:21,886 --> 00:40:26,157
In case you feel
nervous and uncomfortable...

907
00:40:26,224 --> 00:40:27,859
A DUMMY HEAD TO RELIEVE TENSION

908
00:40:29,027 --> 00:40:31,696
PATTING

909
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:33,197
- The water will touch your hair now.
- I'll start.

910
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:34,699
MASTER PARK'S METICULOUS WASH

911
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:36,534
It feels good right now.

912
00:40:37,735 --> 00:40:39,871
- That's great.
- They told me to do this

913
00:40:39,938 --> 00:40:41,306
so water doesn't get into their ears.

914
00:40:41,372 --> 00:40:44,342
DONG-YEON LEARNS IT AS WELL
IN CASE CUSTOMERS LINE UP

915
00:40:44,409 --> 00:40:45,410
Three pumps?

916
00:40:45,476 --> 00:40:46,644
THE RIGHT AMOUNT OF SHAMPOO

917
00:40:46,711 --> 00:40:48,413
This makes a lot of lather.

918
00:40:48,479 --> 00:40:52,383
Once here, once here, once here,
and once on the back.

919
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:54,919
Apparently, this shampoo is
good for thinning hair.

920
00:40:54,986 --> 00:40:58,222
- I see.
- And it helps reduce hair loss.

921
00:40:58,289 --> 00:40:59,290
THICK HAIR

922
00:41:00,525 --> 00:41:02,860
SUPER SATISFIED

923
00:41:03,861 --> 00:41:06,097
A FULL SCALP-CARE SERVICE
PACKED WITH NOURISHMENT

924
00:41:07,165 --> 00:41:08,232
Like this.

925
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:09,667
HIS SCALP ABSORBS THE NUTRIENTS

926
00:41:09,734 --> 00:41:11,736
Apply it like this.

927
00:41:12,870 --> 00:41:14,605
This conditioning mask is

928
00:41:14,672 --> 00:41:16,841
supposed to add volume
at the roots across your hair.

929
00:41:16,908 --> 00:41:20,044
HE LAY DOWN TO LEARN SHAMPOO
AND ENDED UP GETTING A FULL TREATMENT

930
00:41:20,111 --> 00:41:21,779
Your pressure is strong.

931
00:41:23,748 --> 00:41:26,684
HE ONLY NEEDS TO RINSE IT NOW

932
00:41:34,425 --> 00:41:39,097
PLOTTING SOMETHING

933
00:41:40,798 --> 00:41:42,533
SLEEPING PEACEFULLY WITHOUT A CLUE

934
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,969
DROWSY

935
00:41:46,704 --> 00:41:48,840
TURNING ON COLD WATER

936
00:41:50,208 --> 00:41:51,409
DONE

937
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:53,444
PUT IT ON HIS FACE

938
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:54,812
GETTING CLOSE

939
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:57,448
HE WAKES UP

940
00:41:58,016 --> 00:42:01,686
LAUGHING

941
00:42:01,753 --> 00:42:03,054
I'm wide awake now.

942
00:42:03,888 --> 00:42:05,490
EXTRA COLD WATER

943
00:42:05,556 --> 00:42:08,493
Wow, that's so cold.

944
00:42:08,559 --> 00:42:09,594
Hey, you.

945
00:42:10,695 --> 00:42:12,030
I'm awake now.

946
00:42:12,630 --> 00:42:14,499
THE CUSTOMER GIVES IT FIVE STARS

947
00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:15,700
I almost died.

948
00:42:16,334 --> 00:42:17,468
Sorry.

949
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:19,170
HAPPY

950
00:42:20,138 --> 00:42:23,174
We have to decide
business hours, prices...

951
00:42:23,574 --> 00:42:26,177
Here, the sun sets at 5:20 p.m.

952
00:42:26,744 --> 00:42:28,112
Should we close around four?

953
00:42:28,446 --> 00:42:29,514
Is that too early?

954
00:42:29,914 --> 00:42:31,649
Since tomorrow's our first day

955
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:33,885
- Maybe five?
- let's try staying open until five.

956
00:42:33,951 --> 00:42:35,887
- When do we open?
- Then, we adjust it after.

957
00:42:36,287 --> 00:42:38,756
The elders here probably
wake up early, right?

958
00:42:38,823 --> 00:42:40,758
Don't you think they start
their day early?

959
00:42:40,825 --> 00:42:42,360
How about 8 a.m.? Too early?

960
00:42:42,427 --> 00:42:44,295
- Nine or ten.
- Ten?

961
00:42:44,362 --> 00:42:46,230
That's exactly
seven hours of work, right?

962
00:42:46,697 --> 00:42:48,499
FLUSTERED

963
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:50,435
Shouldn't we work
like eight hours a day?

964
00:42:51,702 --> 00:42:54,806
- Then, 9:30 a.m.?
- Should we do 10 to 6? Or 9:30?

965
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:55,873
Nine?

966
00:42:56,574 --> 00:42:58,042
From 9 to 5.

967
00:42:58,109 --> 00:43:00,278
- Nine to nine? I mean, 9 to 5?
- Yes.

968
00:43:01,646 --> 00:43:03,247
- Price.
- Price.

969
00:43:03,314 --> 00:43:04,315
THE MOST IMPORTANT: PRICES

970
00:43:04,916 --> 00:43:06,551
When you think about it

971
00:43:06,984 --> 00:43:09,487
I'm not exactly
a skilled, experienced barber.

972
00:43:09,554 --> 00:43:11,422
I'm only a rookie barber.

973
00:43:11,489 --> 00:43:13,157
Let's do 5,000 won per service.

974
00:43:14,058 --> 00:43:15,059
Haircuts will cost 5,000 won.

975
00:43:15,460 --> 00:43:17,161
- Dyes are 5,000 won.
- Still 5,000 won.

976
00:43:17,662 --> 00:43:19,030
Is that too expensive?

977
00:43:19,097 --> 00:43:20,998
- No, I think it's reasonable.
- Yes.

978
00:43:21,065 --> 00:43:23,067
- It's fine, right?
- I like it.

979
00:43:24,168 --> 00:43:26,537
I won't charge them for the nails.

980
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:29,073
- Free service.
- Yes, it's free.

981
00:43:29,707 --> 00:43:33,044
We're starting as a barbershop

982
00:43:33,111 --> 00:43:35,079
so let's do it
with the heart of learning.

983
00:43:36,247 --> 00:43:38,616
They say there's no hair salon
in this village at all.

984
00:43:38,683 --> 00:43:40,251
- They don't have any.
- Really?

985
00:43:40,318 --> 00:43:45,590
So, it's hard to compare prices.

986
00:43:46,691 --> 00:43:47,692
How about 6,000 won?

987
00:43:49,594 --> 00:43:50,595
VAT included?

988
00:43:51,529 --> 00:43:53,764
- Including VAT?
- Then, it's only 5,500 won.

989
00:43:53,831 --> 00:43:55,066
It is.

990
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:56,701
You're good with numbers.

991
00:43:56,767 --> 00:43:58,870
LAUGHING

992
00:44:00,338 --> 00:44:02,373
SO

993
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:05,009
HOW SHOULD WE SET THE PRICE?

994
00:44:10,248 --> 00:44:13,117
Boss, there's a customer.

995
00:44:13,184 --> 00:44:14,986
Boss, there's a customer.

996
00:44:15,052 --> 00:44:16,387
- Is someone here?
- What is it?

997
00:44:21,726 --> 00:44:24,662
SOMEONE APPROACHES THE SHOP
WITHOUT HESITATION

998
00:44:25,296 --> 00:44:27,665
COULD IT BE A CUSTOMER?

999
00:44:30,168 --> 00:44:32,270
EMERGENCY

1000
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:34,372
IT'S A CUSTOMER

1001
00:44:35,473 --> 00:44:37,508
A CUSTOMER WALKS IN
WHILE THEY'RE STILL GETTING READY

1002
00:44:37,575 --> 00:44:39,076
- Hello.
- Hello.

1003
00:44:39,143 --> 00:44:40,411
- Hello.
- Hello, ma'am.

1004
00:44:41,279 --> 00:44:42,847
- Hello.
- Hello.

1005
00:44:42,914 --> 00:44:46,117
BIG TROUBLE
THEY'RE NOT EVEN READY YET!

1006
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:48,352
Hi, you've been remodeling
this house for a while.

1007
00:44:48,419 --> 00:44:50,721
- Oh, you live next door.
- Yes, it was so noisy.

1008
00:44:50,788 --> 00:44:52,657
Sorry for the trouble, ma'am.

1009
00:44:52,723 --> 00:44:53,791
- Hello.
- Come on in.

1010
00:44:53,858 --> 00:44:55,426
- Come in.
- We're not open yet, but...

1011
00:44:55,493 --> 00:44:58,663
It was so noisy,
but I'm glad it's finished now.

1012
00:44:58,729 --> 00:45:02,133
- Yes.
- I heard you could do my hair.

1013
00:45:03,601 --> 00:45:07,205
SHE WAS GOING TO TELL HIM OFF, BUT...

1014
00:45:08,506 --> 00:45:09,507
Goodness.

1015
00:45:10,241 --> 00:45:12,944
Everyone is dying to see you.

1016
00:45:13,211 --> 00:45:14,812
- Our shop...
- Long ago

1017
00:45:14,879 --> 00:45:17,215
I think I saw you once
when you played Go.

1018
00:45:17,281 --> 00:45:19,984
You had a match
with a little kid, right?

1019
00:45:20,985 --> 00:45:22,019
- What was it?
- On a TV show?

1020
00:45:22,086 --> 00:45:24,322
- Yes, on a TV show.
- Yes, you're right.

1021
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:25,489
You're all handsome.

1022
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:27,391
Feel free to take a seat.

1023
00:45:27,458 --> 00:45:30,294
- But we're not properly open yet.
- Right.

1024
00:45:30,361 --> 00:45:31,796
- We're setting things up.
- A soft opening.

1025
00:45:32,430 --> 00:45:34,498
- It's a soft opening.
- Have you been inside before?

1026
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:35,766
Am I the first one to come in?

1027
00:45:35,833 --> 00:45:37,401
- You're our first customer.
- You're our first.

1028
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:39,237
- Welcome.
- I live right here.

1029
00:45:39,303 --> 00:45:40,471
- Right next door?
- Yes.

1030
00:45:41,272 --> 00:45:42,640
May I ask your name?

1031
00:45:42,707 --> 00:45:43,874
Kim Jeong-ja.

1032
00:45:43,941 --> 00:45:45,710
Mrs. Kim Jeong-ja.

1033
00:45:46,310 --> 00:45:47,345
- How should I...
- Sister.

1034
00:45:47,411 --> 00:45:48,412
Sister?

1035
00:45:48,479 --> 00:45:49,480
- How should I...
- Sister.

1036
00:45:49,547 --> 00:45:51,249
Sister?

1037
00:45:51,315 --> 00:45:52,316
- Miss Jeong-ja.
- All right.

1038
00:45:57,154 --> 00:46:00,024
SHE LIVES RIGHT NEXT DOOR
TO THE BARBERSHOP

1039
00:46:01,025 --> 00:46:03,194
SHE WAS DRAWN IN BY THE NOISY SOUNDS

1040
00:46:03,661 --> 00:46:05,263
DID THEY OPEN TODAY?

1041
00:46:05,830 --> 00:46:08,232
GOING TO TAKE A LOOK

1042
00:46:09,267 --> 00:46:10,735
OUR UNOFFICIAL FIRST CUSTOMER,
KIM JEONG-JA

1043
00:46:10,801 --> 00:46:12,103
- Customer.
- Take a seat.

1044
00:46:12,169 --> 00:46:13,537
Please.

1045
00:46:14,405 --> 00:46:16,440
FIDGETING

1046
00:46:17,908 --> 00:46:21,412
- Do you want your hair done now?
- No.

1047
00:46:21,479 --> 00:46:24,081
- My granddaughter
- Yes.

1048
00:46:24,482 --> 00:46:26,183
is coming to meet me.

1049
00:46:26,250 --> 00:46:28,052
She's getting married in February.

1050
00:46:28,452 --> 00:46:29,720
- She's coming with the groom-to-be.
- Really?

1051
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:32,590
So, it'd be nice
if you could make me pretty.

1052
00:46:32,657 --> 00:46:33,758
MAKE ME PRETTY

1053
00:46:33,824 --> 00:46:35,326
- That would be great.
- Yes.

1054
00:46:35,393 --> 00:46:37,361
- All right. On Saturday.
- When? Saturday?

1055
00:46:37,428 --> 00:46:39,897
- Saturday.
- You can visit on Saturday, then.

1056
00:46:39,964 --> 00:46:41,666
- I'll blow-dry and style your hair.
- Sure.

1057
00:46:41,732 --> 00:46:44,235
- We can also dye your hair.
- Okay, that sounds nice.

1058
00:46:44,302 --> 00:46:45,303
It's all grey now.

1059
00:46:45,369 --> 00:46:47,471
- Is it?
- We can dye it for you.

1060
00:46:48,272 --> 00:46:49,573
- Your hair...
- We put

1061
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,009
- a pellet boiler.
- We can help you.

1062
00:46:52,076 --> 00:46:54,011
I flung the door open
and burned all my hair.

1063
00:46:54,078 --> 00:46:55,546
Oh, no.

1064
00:46:55,946 --> 00:46:57,214
It all got burnt up.

1065
00:46:57,281 --> 00:46:59,283
- Oh, no. It's damaged.
- Yes.

1066
00:46:59,784 --> 00:47:01,018
He'll take good care of you.

1067
00:47:01,085 --> 00:47:02,987
- I'll do my best.
- Oh, dear.

1068
00:47:04,021 --> 00:47:06,490
HOW IS HE SO SWEET WHEN HE TALKS

1069
00:47:06,557 --> 00:47:08,559
Is it true that there isn't
a barbershop or a salon

1070
00:47:08,626 --> 00:47:10,828
- in this town?
- None.

1071
00:47:12,063 --> 00:47:14,198
Then, where do you go
to get your hair done?

1072
00:47:14,265 --> 00:47:15,266
To Muju.

1073
00:47:16,067 --> 00:47:18,102
- Aren't we in Muju?
- Isn't this Muju?

1074
00:47:18,169 --> 00:47:19,470
To Muju-eup.

1075
00:47:19,537 --> 00:47:22,039
Oh, Muju-eup.
Which district are we in?

1076
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:24,675
This is Apseom Village, Naedo-ri.

1077
00:47:24,742 --> 00:47:26,510
- Naedo-ri near the Geumgang River.
- Yes. Geumgang River.

1078
00:47:26,577 --> 00:47:27,712
A SMALL VILLAGE
WITH NO SALON OR BARBERSHOP

1079
00:47:28,279 --> 00:47:31,182
THEY MUST WAIT FOR A BUS
THAT COMES EVERY 140 MINUTES

1080
00:47:32,216 --> 00:47:35,653
THE HASSLE OF GOING DOWNTOWN

1081
00:47:36,821 --> 00:47:42,259
THE VILLAGERS MAY HAVE BEEN WAITING
FOR A PLACE LIKE THIS

1082
00:47:42,827 --> 00:47:45,162
But you'll charge money
for hair, right?

1083
00:47:45,629 --> 00:47:47,398
- That's right.
- How much do you charge?

1084
00:47:48,466 --> 00:47:51,769
How much is a haircut
at salons in Muju?

1085
00:47:51,836 --> 00:47:54,205
In Muju-gun

1086
00:47:54,605 --> 00:47:57,808
a haircut can cost 10,000 won.

1087
00:47:57,875 --> 00:47:59,643
- They're all different.
- Yes.

1088
00:47:59,710 --> 00:48:03,647
Then, how much would make you feel
like it's worth the money?

1089
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:06,517
It'd be nice to pay only 5,000 won.

1090
00:48:07,017 --> 00:48:08,419
ALMOST EXACTLY
WHAT THE THREE WERE THINKING

1091
00:48:08,486 --> 00:48:10,621
- So 5,000 won.
- Only 5,000 won.

1092
00:48:10,688 --> 00:48:12,223
- Around that.
- Thanks for asking.

1093
00:48:12,957 --> 00:48:14,759
Would you like a small gift?

1094
00:48:14,825 --> 00:48:16,527
- From us.
- What gift?

1095
00:48:16,594 --> 00:48:17,595
It's incredible.

1096
00:48:17,661 --> 00:48:19,764
- Please remember us.
- Of course.

1097
00:48:19,830 --> 00:48:22,533
- It's a towel.
- I see.

1098
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:26,270
PLEASE SPREAD THE WORD ABOUT US

1099
00:48:27,938 --> 00:48:30,975
ACTING CUTE FOR PROMOTION

1100
00:48:31,876 --> 00:48:34,345
- We paint your nails, too.
- Right, make them pretty.

1101
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:35,880
What's your favorite color?

1102
00:48:36,981 --> 00:48:39,383
Something simple.

1103
00:48:39,450 --> 00:48:42,420
- Something simple.
- Not too red.

1104
00:48:42,486 --> 00:48:45,890
If an old lady is all flashy,
it's kind of...

1105
00:48:45,956 --> 00:48:48,159
- No.
- Make it subtle.

1106
00:48:48,225 --> 00:48:50,161
- You're still so young.
- I'm young.

1107
00:48:50,227 --> 00:48:51,228
- You bet.
- You bet.

1108
00:48:51,729 --> 00:48:53,364
You're still young, miss.

1109
00:48:53,431 --> 00:48:55,032
PLAYFUL FLATTERY

1110
00:48:55,900 --> 00:48:57,334
Oh, dear.

1111
00:48:57,401 --> 00:48:59,503
You're praising me so much
that I almost feel sorry.

1112
00:49:01,705 --> 00:49:02,807
Make yourself at home.

1113
00:49:02,873 --> 00:49:04,074
- Thanks.
- Miss Jeong-ja.

1114
00:49:04,141 --> 00:49:05,709
Thank you for calling me by my name.

1115
00:49:10,614 --> 00:49:11,615
It felt...

1116
00:49:12,183 --> 00:49:14,452
It felt strange.
It made me emotional.

1117
00:49:14,919 --> 00:49:16,187
At some point

1118
00:49:17,321 --> 00:49:21,859
she was probably called
someone's mom or someone's grandma.

1119
00:49:22,593 --> 00:49:25,729
I'm glad I called her by her name.
"Miss Jeong-ja" was a good call.

1120
00:49:25,796 --> 00:49:26,831
CALLING HER NAME MAKES
THEM FEEL CLOSER

1121
00:49:26,897 --> 00:49:27,998
Do you have any food?

1122
00:49:28,065 --> 00:49:30,601
We should, but we were going
to eat ramyeon later.

1123
00:49:30,801 --> 00:49:32,470
POOR KIDS

1124
00:49:33,370 --> 00:49:34,839
Would you like some ramyeon?

1125
00:49:34,905 --> 00:49:35,906
I don't eat ramyeon.

1126
00:49:36,474 --> 00:49:38,242
- You can't ask for a bite later.
- I won't.

1127
00:49:38,742 --> 00:49:40,711
I don't eat ramyeon.

1128
00:49:41,946 --> 00:49:44,114
Ma'am, can we have some
of your kimchi?

1129
00:49:44,181 --> 00:49:45,182
- Kimchi?
- Yes.

1130
00:49:45,249 --> 00:49:47,017
Sure. I'll bring you a head.

1131
00:49:47,084 --> 00:49:48,285
I'LL BRING A WHOLE HEAD

1132
00:49:48,352 --> 00:49:50,387
- Thank you.
- My kimchi doesn't taste that good.

1133
00:49:50,454 --> 00:49:53,324
Come on. I can finish a whole bowl
of rice with kimchi alone.

1134
00:49:53,958 --> 00:49:55,192
Should I bring it now?

1135
00:49:55,693 --> 00:49:57,428
I'll come with you.

1136
00:50:10,608 --> 00:50:12,276
- I'll go and get kimchi.
- Okay.

1137
00:50:13,577 --> 00:50:14,578
- Let's go.
- Yes.

1138
00:50:14,645 --> 00:50:17,047
- We can do it when you're back.
- Okay.

1139
00:50:17,114 --> 00:50:18,749
- Where's your jacket?
- That's fine.

1140
00:50:18,816 --> 00:50:19,817
Okay.

1141
00:50:20,784 --> 00:50:23,220
- It's right next door.
- It is.

1142
00:50:23,287 --> 00:50:24,989
My house is a mess.

1143
00:50:25,523 --> 00:50:29,827
- How long have you lived here?
- Ever since I married in.

1144
00:50:29,894 --> 00:50:31,195
- Really?
- Yes.

1145
00:50:31,929 --> 00:50:34,198
Do you remember?
The first time I came here, you said

1146
00:50:34,265 --> 00:50:37,801
"Styrofoam is flying around
over there."

1147
00:50:38,235 --> 00:50:40,004
- Did I?
- Yes.

1148
00:50:40,070 --> 00:50:41,672
- Oh, boy.
- Should I wait here?

1149
00:50:41,739 --> 00:50:42,973
- No, come in.
- Is that okay?

1150
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,842
- Yes.
- Excuse me.

1151
00:50:44,909 --> 00:50:46,377
The house is a mess.

1152
00:50:46,443 --> 00:50:48,312
- Still...
- That's how country houses are.

1153
00:50:49,680 --> 00:50:50,848
Excuse me.

1154
00:50:50,915 --> 00:50:51,916
FIRST ENCOUNTER BUT FEELS FAMILIAR

1155
00:50:52,316 --> 00:50:53,651
It's cozy.

1156
00:50:54,552 --> 00:50:56,020
It's a cozy home.

1157
00:50:57,421 --> 00:51:00,224
- When people come to my house,
- Yes.

1158
00:51:00,291 --> 00:51:01,759
they say it smells warm.

1159
00:51:01,825 --> 00:51:03,193
- It does.
- Yes.

1160
00:51:03,928 --> 00:51:05,362
- Should I put it here?
- Sure.

1161
00:51:05,429 --> 00:51:06,864
THE COZY FEELING
OF VISITING GRANDMA'S HOUSE

1162
00:51:07,598 --> 00:51:08,832
I washed the comforter.

1163
00:51:09,266 --> 00:51:10,267
GRUNTING

1164
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:16,106
ENTERING THE MYSTERIOUS KIMCHI ZONE

1165
00:51:16,173 --> 00:51:18,842
Where is she?
Where did you go to get kimchi?

1166
00:51:22,846 --> 00:51:24,148
Oh, you have a kimchi fridge.

1167
00:51:24,214 --> 00:51:27,217
- That looks delicious.
- The house is so small

1168
00:51:27,585 --> 00:51:29,320
so there's nowhere to put it.

1169
00:51:29,386 --> 00:51:32,623
I used lots of salted seafood
and salted shrimp.

1170
00:51:32,690 --> 00:51:34,558
GETTING MISS JEONG-JA'S KIMCHI

1171
00:51:34,625 --> 00:51:36,093
That looks delicious.

1172
00:51:36,594 --> 00:51:38,062
THE CONTAINER IS FULL,
BUT SHE ADDS ONE MORE

1173
00:51:38,128 --> 00:51:39,129
One more.

1174
00:51:39,196 --> 00:51:40,464
- Thank you.
- Yes.

1175
00:51:40,531 --> 00:51:41,632
It looks so tasty.

1176
00:51:41,699 --> 00:51:44,101
- You'll have to taste it first.
- It already looks good.

1177
00:51:48,205 --> 00:51:53,744
- You're really good with elders.
- No, I'm trying.

1178
00:51:54,144 --> 00:51:55,713
You looked

1179
00:51:56,547 --> 00:51:57,815
super experienced.

1180
00:51:57,881 --> 00:52:00,317
- It was effort.
- That's impressive.

1181
00:52:00,384 --> 00:52:02,219
SANG-YI LOOKED EXPERIENCED,
BUT IT TOOK EFFORT

1182
00:52:02,286 --> 00:52:04,588
- Right.
- Are you making fish-shaped buns?

1183
00:52:04,655 --> 00:52:05,689
Yes, fish-shaped buns.

1184
00:52:05,756 --> 00:52:08,225
When was the last time you had one?

1185
00:52:08,292 --> 00:52:10,027
I've never tried it.

1186
00:52:10,094 --> 00:52:11,128
- Not once?
- Yes.

1187
00:52:11,195 --> 00:52:13,130
- You've never had fish-shaped buns?
- No.

1188
00:52:13,530 --> 00:52:14,765
No one ever gave me one.

1189
00:52:14,832 --> 00:52:17,801
- No, I meant in your life.
- No.

1190
00:52:17,868 --> 00:52:19,203
I ate a lot in Muju.

1191
00:52:19,269 --> 00:52:20,270
- I meant here.
- Right?

1192
00:52:20,337 --> 00:52:21,739
You really startled me.

1193
00:52:22,206 --> 00:52:24,141
I thought you had never tried it.

1194
00:52:24,441 --> 00:52:26,310
They're just fish-shaped buns.

1195
00:52:26,777 --> 00:52:28,779
She gave us
like three heads of kimchi.

1196
00:52:29,913 --> 00:52:30,948
It looks good.

1197
00:52:31,915 --> 00:52:33,350
SLURPING

1198
00:52:34,218 --> 00:52:36,820
- Thank you for the kimchi, ma'am.
- Thank you!

1199
00:52:36,887 --> 00:52:38,789
I don't know if it'll taste any good.

1200
00:52:38,856 --> 00:52:41,458
When was the last time
you painted your nails?

1201
00:52:42,159 --> 00:52:46,463
In winter, when I'm taking a break

1202
00:52:46,530 --> 00:52:48,532
because it doesn't come off easily.

1203
00:52:48,599 --> 00:52:50,901
In the summer, I go out to the field.

1204
00:52:50,968 --> 00:52:55,406
- You have to work.
- I'm always picking flowers.

1205
00:52:55,472 --> 00:52:58,342
The peach blossoms bloom fully.

1206
00:52:59,109 --> 00:53:00,444
This is a peach orchard area.

1207
00:53:00,511 --> 00:53:02,513
- Peaches.
- The peaches get this big.

1208
00:53:02,579 --> 00:53:03,947
There are so many.

1209
00:53:04,014 --> 00:53:07,051
- I guess the soil is good here.
- It's unbelievably tough.

1210
00:53:07,117 --> 00:53:11,055
I don't think I can do it anymore.
My son has to come and help.

1211
00:53:11,689 --> 00:53:16,593
- When does it end? Which season?
- Around October or November.

1212
00:53:16,660 --> 00:53:18,262
It ends in October.

1213
00:53:18,328 --> 00:53:21,965
- So it's been a month or two.
- Yes.

1214
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:24,702
THEN

1215
00:53:24,768 --> 00:53:26,270
Then, you can get a manicure.

1216
00:53:27,037 --> 00:53:31,709
- Well, my hands are not decent.
- They'll be like a princess's hands.

1217
00:53:31,775 --> 00:53:35,279
Just as a sample,
we'll do a simple manicure today.

1218
00:53:35,879 --> 00:53:37,748
- Okay.
- You're my first customer ever.

1219
00:53:37,815 --> 00:53:41,385
- Yes. Oh, my.
- Miss Jeong-ja, you're my first.

1220
00:53:41,852 --> 00:53:43,454
- Since you came today,
- Yes?

1221
00:53:43,787 --> 00:53:45,522
please spread the word around.

1222
00:53:45,589 --> 00:53:46,890
- Spread it a lot?
- A lot.

1223
00:53:49,660 --> 00:53:51,128
I WILL WIN HER OVER WITH NAILS

1224
00:53:51,195 --> 00:53:52,196
That's a lot.

1225
00:53:52,629 --> 00:53:54,798
- Oh, my.
- There's a ton.

1226
00:53:54,865 --> 00:53:58,035
I'll go brag
at the village hall after this.

1227
00:53:58,102 --> 00:53:59,737
Go and show them off.

1228
00:54:01,772 --> 00:54:03,941
- Tell me if it hurts.
- Okay.

1229
00:54:05,008 --> 00:54:06,710
Sometimes

1230
00:54:07,845 --> 00:54:08,979
if you mess up

1231
00:54:09,379 --> 00:54:10,781
it can end up bleed.

1232
00:54:10,848 --> 00:54:13,484
- Don't make me bleed.
- But I'll make sure it never bleeds.

1233
00:54:14,785 --> 00:54:16,620
I can't cook if it bleeds.

1234
00:54:17,287 --> 00:54:19,389
When did you move to Muju?

1235
00:54:19,456 --> 00:54:20,524
- Me?
- Yes.

1236
00:54:21,225 --> 00:54:22,659
I got married at 22.

1237
00:54:22,726 --> 00:54:24,128
- You married in?
- Yes.

1238
00:54:24,194 --> 00:54:25,829
My husband got married at 20.

1239
00:54:26,463 --> 00:54:28,999
- He's younger than me.
- Oh, my.

1240
00:54:29,066 --> 00:54:30,768
We've got a legend in the shop.

1241
00:54:30,834 --> 00:54:32,336
A LEGEND AHEAD OF HER TIME

1242
00:54:32,402 --> 00:54:34,905
Legend or not, I'm just a farmer.

1243
00:54:34,972 --> 00:54:38,475
BACK TO THE MAIN JOB
HIS FIRST MANICURE APPLICATION

1244
00:54:40,144 --> 00:54:44,047
TREMBLING

1245
00:54:45,449 --> 00:54:46,984
It's my first time
doing it on a real customer.

1246
00:54:48,619 --> 00:54:51,455
- I'm honestly a bit nervous.
- It's okay.

1247
00:54:51,955 --> 00:54:54,758
There's nothing to be nervous about.
Have confidence and do it.

1248
00:54:55,459 --> 00:54:57,027
- Okay, sis.
- It's fine if it's ugly

1249
00:54:57,094 --> 00:54:58,662
and it's fine if it's pretty.

1250
00:55:01,031 --> 00:55:03,500
My hands are all dark and puffy.

1251
00:55:03,734 --> 00:55:06,904
No matter what you put on,
they don't look fancy.

1252
00:55:06,970 --> 00:55:08,038
Not at all.

1253
00:55:08,105 --> 00:55:11,975
I will make you shine
with your nails.

1254
00:55:12,843 --> 00:55:14,678
SHY

1255
00:55:15,212 --> 00:55:17,314
That's a beautiful color.

1256
00:55:17,681 --> 00:55:20,017
- She picked it herself.
- It's like cherry blossoms.

1257
00:55:20,484 --> 00:55:23,754
What if my husband doesn't recognize
me because they're so pretty?

1258
00:55:23,821 --> 00:55:25,422
Don't make me too pretty.

1259
00:55:25,489 --> 00:55:27,791
It's going to get wild.

1260
00:55:29,526 --> 00:55:30,594
MEANWHILE IN THE KITCHEN

1261
00:55:30,661 --> 00:55:33,530
JJAMPPONG RAMYEON IS BOILING

1262
00:55:35,599 --> 00:55:37,134
- BO GUM.
- Yes?

1263
00:55:37,768 --> 00:55:39,369
It looks like it's done.

1264
00:55:39,436 --> 00:55:41,238
That looks scrumptious.

1265
00:55:41,305 --> 00:55:42,973
WITH THE KIMCHI THEY GOT
FROM MISS JEONG-JA

1266
00:55:43,040 --> 00:55:44,474
You said you hadn't eaten, right?

1267
00:55:44,541 --> 00:55:46,143
- I ate.
- She ate.

1268
00:55:49,479 --> 00:55:52,115
THE THREE BROTHERS HAVE BEEN STARVING
FOR NEARLY 15 HOURS

1269
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:55,319
AN EYE-OPENING BURST OF FLAVOR

1270
00:55:56,653 --> 00:55:57,754
It's insanely good.

1271
00:55:57,821 --> 00:55:58,822
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

1272
00:55:59,289 --> 00:56:02,259
WHEN IS SANG-YI COMING?

1273
00:56:02,326 --> 00:56:04,661
- Hurry and go eat.
- Let me finish this.

1274
00:56:04,728 --> 00:56:06,463
- Just your pinky.
- No, eat first.

1275
00:56:06,530 --> 00:56:08,298
I'll go home and come back
while you eat.

1276
00:56:08,365 --> 00:56:10,267
Go and eat. You must be hungry.

1277
00:56:10,334 --> 00:56:11,835
Go on. Leave that.

1278
00:56:11,902 --> 00:56:13,170
Don't touch it.

1279
00:56:13,237 --> 00:56:16,240
- We'll let them dry, then.
- Sure.

1280
00:56:19,443 --> 00:56:20,978
I was actually starving.

1281
00:56:21,178 --> 00:56:22,579
Let me wash my hands first.

1282
00:56:23,447 --> 00:56:26,984
Isn't that aged kimchi?
That's amazing.

1283
00:56:27,050 --> 00:56:29,653
- It's not aged kimchi.
- It's not?

1284
00:56:30,487 --> 00:56:32,489
GLANCING

1285
00:56:32,556 --> 00:56:34,892
- Please rest, miss.
- Okay.

1286
00:56:34,958 --> 00:56:35,959
WORRIED SHE MIGHT GET BORED

1287
00:56:36,026 --> 00:56:37,361
Should we play some music?

1288
00:56:37,427 --> 00:56:38,896
You're bored, aren't you?
How are you doing?

1289
00:56:38,962 --> 00:56:40,530
I'm doing fine.

1290
00:56:40,597 --> 00:56:43,767
- Would you like a cup of tea?
- No, just go and eat.

1291
00:56:43,834 --> 00:56:45,636
PLEASE GO AND EAT

1292
00:56:45,702 --> 00:56:48,839
- The cabbage is so good.
- Cabbage?

1293
00:56:49,773 --> 00:56:52,609
THE REALITY OF SMALL BUSINESS OWNERS

1294
00:56:57,147 --> 00:56:59,316
BLINKING

1295
00:57:01,919 --> 00:57:04,054
GLANCING AROUND

1296
00:57:10,661 --> 00:57:13,997
I THINK I MIGHT BE LONELY

1297
00:57:14,064 --> 00:57:15,532
The kimchi is too good.

1298
00:57:17,534 --> 00:57:18,969
Ma'am, your kimchi is so good.

1299
00:57:19,036 --> 00:57:20,938
- Do you like it?
- I love it.

1300
00:57:21,505 --> 00:57:23,006
I don't know if it's any good.

1301
00:57:24,074 --> 00:57:25,709
GLANCING

1302
00:57:26,510 --> 00:57:30,914
THEY SLURP THE SOUP IN ONE GO

1303
00:57:31,982 --> 00:57:33,450
THEN HURRY BACK

1304
00:57:33,517 --> 00:57:34,584
Then

1305
00:57:34,651 --> 00:57:37,087
when will your husband come home
after having noodles?

1306
00:57:37,154 --> 00:57:38,221
HE TAKES HIS SEAT NATURALLY

1307
00:57:38,288 --> 00:57:39,723
He'll come whenever he pleases.

1308
00:57:39,790 --> 00:57:41,825
You don't eat dinner together
when he's back?

1309
00:57:42,626 --> 00:57:46,163
Sang-yi has become
best friends with her.

1310
00:57:47,631 --> 00:57:50,467
SOMEONE ELSE IS APPROACHING
THE BARBERSHOP

1311
00:57:53,136 --> 00:57:54,738
Hello.

1312
00:57:54,805 --> 00:57:56,673
- Hello.
- Hi.

1313
00:57:56,740 --> 00:57:58,108
Here comes the village chief!

1314
00:57:58,175 --> 00:57:59,843
- Oh, he's the village chief.
- Yes.

1315
00:57:59,910 --> 00:58:01,478
The chief of our village.

1316
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:04,881
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

1317
00:58:04,948 --> 00:58:06,283
- Hello.
- Hi.

1318
00:58:06,350 --> 00:58:08,218
- You're the first one.
- Hello.

1319
00:58:08,285 --> 00:58:09,653
- It's a pleasure.
- The village chief.

1320
00:58:09,720 --> 00:58:11,021
- Nice to meet you.
- I'm Lee Sang-yi.

1321
00:58:11,088 --> 00:58:12,889
When the crew was
remodeling the place

1322
00:58:12,956 --> 00:58:15,325
I came by a few times,
and it looked like it was done.

1323
00:58:15,392 --> 00:58:16,760
- Oh, this place?
- Yes.

1324
00:58:16,827 --> 00:58:18,128
- It's nice and warm here.
- Oh, right.

1325
00:58:18,195 --> 00:58:19,229
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

1326
00:58:19,296 --> 00:58:20,497
ANOTHER HANDSHAKE

1327
00:58:20,564 --> 00:58:22,499
The place is

1328
00:58:23,467 --> 00:58:26,470
so pretty and cool,
like you young folks.

1329
00:58:26,536 --> 00:58:28,972
It really is.
The boiler works great, too.

1330
00:58:29,473 --> 00:58:32,009
I think the residents will love it.

1331
00:58:32,075 --> 00:58:33,276
That's a relief.

1332
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:34,544
This house

1333
00:58:34,611 --> 00:58:36,246
is going to be famous now.

1334
00:58:37,180 --> 00:58:38,915
- It'll be famous.
- Ma'am

1335
00:58:38,982 --> 00:58:40,517
you came before me.

1336
00:58:40,584 --> 00:58:42,519
- She's our first customer.
- I'm their first customer.

1337
00:58:42,586 --> 00:58:44,021
- She lives next door.
- She is

1338
00:58:44,087 --> 00:58:47,491
the comedian and announcer
in this village.

1339
00:58:47,557 --> 00:58:49,626
I told you not to say
things like that.

1340
00:58:51,361 --> 00:58:52,362
Also...

1341
00:58:52,429 --> 00:58:53,430
SMACKING HIS LIPS

1342
00:58:53,497 --> 00:58:54,731
...she's the first one, right?

1343
00:58:54,798 --> 00:58:56,299
- Your first customer?
- Our very first.

1344
00:58:56,366 --> 00:58:57,467
ASKING THE SAME QUESTION AGAIN

1345
00:58:57,968 --> 00:58:59,036
Really?

1346
00:58:59,102 --> 00:59:00,570
HE RAN OUT OF QUESTIONS

1347
00:59:01,171 --> 00:59:03,006
AHEM

1348
00:59:04,141 --> 00:59:05,942
- Have you eaten?
- Yes.

1349
00:59:07,077 --> 00:59:09,179
I'm the chief of this village.

1350
00:59:09,246 --> 00:59:11,515
LOOKS LIKE HE HAS
SOMETHING HE WANTS TO SAY

1351
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:14,117
You've set things up so nicely

1352
00:59:14,184 --> 00:59:16,753
so I've been waiting for you
to call me.

1353
00:59:20,023 --> 00:59:25,262
I thought you could use my help,
so I came by on purpose.

1354
00:59:25,328 --> 00:59:27,964
Then, after we finish up tomorrow

1355
00:59:28,031 --> 00:59:30,434
since we don't really know
the neighborhood

1356
00:59:30,500 --> 00:59:32,002
we want to greet each household.

1357
00:59:32,069 --> 00:59:33,837
- Could you introduce us?
- Of course.

1358
00:59:33,904 --> 00:59:36,673
- But they have that broadcast.
- The announcement system.

1359
00:59:36,740 --> 00:59:38,909
- Oh, right.
- In the countryside...

1360
00:59:38,975 --> 00:59:40,844
Without being awkward or too much.

1361
00:59:40,911 --> 00:59:42,412
What's that sound?

1362
00:59:45,782 --> 00:59:48,552
THE VILLAGE BROADCAST
THEY HEARD EARLIER

1363
00:59:49,019 --> 00:59:50,454
Broadcasting isn't that hard.

1364
00:59:50,887 --> 00:59:52,522
You can do it with a phone.

1365
00:59:52,589 --> 00:59:53,723
- Really?
- On your phone?

1366
00:59:53,790 --> 00:59:54,925
We do it with a phone.

1367
00:59:54,991 --> 00:59:55,992
- Right here?
- Really?

1368
00:59:56,059 --> 00:59:58,128
- You can do it right here? Really?
- Yes.

1369
00:59:58,195 --> 00:59:59,229
Please make an announcement.

1370
00:59:59,296 --> 01:00:02,799
Our village chief
can start things off.

1371
01:00:03,133 --> 01:00:04,134
And then...

1372
01:00:04,201 --> 01:00:06,770
You need to keep quiet
when I'm broadcasting

1373
01:00:07,737 --> 01:00:08,738
or your voice will be on air.

1374
01:00:08,805 --> 01:00:09,940
- Will it?
- Yes.

1375
01:00:11,508 --> 01:00:12,976
HANDS TREMBLING
VILLAGE BROADCASTING

1376
01:00:13,043 --> 01:00:14,511
Preparing to broadcast.

1377
01:00:14,578 --> 01:00:16,546
Please wait for a moment.

1378
01:00:17,781 --> 01:00:18,782
It's working.

1379
01:00:21,485 --> 01:00:22,486
AMAZED

1380
01:00:22,552 --> 01:00:24,154
May I have your attention, please?

1381
01:00:25,355 --> 01:00:27,124
Some young men from Seoul

1382
01:00:27,624 --> 01:00:31,795
opened The Village Barber business
that offers haircuts.

1383
01:00:33,363 --> 01:00:39,269
Business hours begin
at 9 a.m. tomorrow morning

1384
01:00:39,870 --> 01:00:41,705
and close at 5 p.m.

1385
01:00:41,771 --> 01:00:43,707
COMMUNITY CENTER FOR ELDERLY WOMEN

1386
01:00:43,773 --> 01:00:48,011
MEANWHILE, AT THE COMMUNITY CENTER
FOR THE ELDERLY

1387
01:00:48,078 --> 01:00:50,514
Really? I should drop by.

1388
01:00:50,580 --> 01:00:53,783
AT THE VILLAGE HALL AS WELL

1389
01:00:53,850 --> 01:00:55,051
IT MUST BE THAT PLACE OVER THERE

1390
01:00:55,118 --> 01:00:57,888
Do come by
and spend time at your leisure.

1391
01:00:58,455 --> 01:01:01,291
Do come by
and spend time at your leisure.

1392
01:01:01,358 --> 01:01:03,693
Also, offer them lots of support.

1393
01:01:04,227 --> 01:01:05,228
Thank you.

1394
01:01:05,862 --> 01:01:06,963
That's how you...

1395
01:01:08,698 --> 01:01:10,033
That's how you...

1396
01:01:10,700 --> 01:01:12,169
RED ALERT
A BROADCAST MISHAP

1397
01:01:12,235 --> 01:01:13,603
HUSH

1398
01:01:16,273 --> 01:01:17,741
Then you turn it off.

1399
01:01:18,575 --> 01:01:20,844
- That's so fascinating.
- That was fascinating.

1400
01:01:20,911 --> 01:01:22,646
- I loved that.
- Thank you.

1401
01:01:22,712 --> 01:01:25,048
- Thank you, sir.
- Oh, dear. It fell off.

1402
01:01:25,115 --> 01:01:26,416
- Thank you.
- Merry Christmas.

1403
01:01:26,483 --> 01:01:28,218
- Get home safely.
- Thank you, sir.

1404
01:01:28,752 --> 01:01:31,154
- You're all so cool.
- Thank you.

1405
01:01:31,721 --> 01:01:32,756
Goodbye.

1406
01:01:34,291 --> 01:01:37,827
SHOULD I NOT HAVE DONE A THUMBS-UP?

1407
01:01:38,929 --> 01:01:39,930
So...

1408
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:43,600
I had no idea you were
the local comedian.

1409
01:01:43,667 --> 01:01:47,571
Me? I am not. Why did he say that?

1410
01:01:47,637 --> 01:01:51,775
- Ma'am, we figured out your secret.
- It's nothing like that at all.

1411
01:01:51,841 --> 01:01:53,610
THE MANICURE IS ALMOST DONE

1412
01:01:53,677 --> 01:01:55,145
It's nice and pretty.

1413
01:01:56,112 --> 01:01:57,347
It's pretty.

1414
01:01:59,049 --> 01:02:03,620
Let me have a final look
to make sure everything's well done.

1415
01:02:03,687 --> 01:02:04,721
It's pretty.

1416
01:02:04,788 --> 01:02:06,289
Your peach-picking hands
look like peaches.

1417
01:02:06,356 --> 01:02:09,292
- You're right.
- They turned into peachy hands.

1418
01:02:09,359 --> 01:02:11,127
How about a high-five to finish up?

1419
01:02:11,528 --> 01:02:12,562
A high-five.

1420
01:02:13,196 --> 01:02:14,531
They look so pretty.

1421
01:02:14,731 --> 01:02:15,765
They're so pretty.

1422
01:02:15,832 --> 01:02:18,301
They look so nice
now that my nails are painted.

1423
01:02:18,368 --> 01:02:19,569
YOU LOOK GOOD, TOO

1424
01:02:19,636 --> 01:02:21,504
Come and get them done
whenever you want.

1425
01:02:21,571 --> 01:02:23,840
I'll go to the village hall
to show them off.

1426
01:02:23,907 --> 01:02:26,876
- Thank you very much.
- Not at all.

1427
01:02:27,310 --> 01:02:29,045
It feels weird to see off a customer.

1428
01:02:30,180 --> 01:02:32,215
It feels like
I actually served her for real.

1429
01:02:32,282 --> 01:02:34,818
- We had only served one customer.
- Yes.

1430
01:02:34,884 --> 01:02:36,886
But it feels like
we went through a storm.

1431
01:02:38,355 --> 01:02:40,523
We must've been tense
without realizing it.

1432
01:02:40,590 --> 01:02:42,259
- It must've weighed on us.
- I guess so.

1433
01:02:42,325 --> 01:02:44,361
THE THREE BROTHERS
SURVIVED THEIR OWN BATTLES

1434
01:02:44,427 --> 01:02:46,029
- Shall we dress up and go out?
- Let's.

1435
01:02:46,096 --> 01:02:47,731
Let's go. I brought five of each.

1436
01:02:49,199 --> 01:02:50,567
Let's get going.

1437
01:02:50,634 --> 01:02:52,636
WE HAVE A BARBERSHOP NOW

1438
01:02:54,004 --> 01:02:55,772
How are you, sir?

1439
01:02:56,573 --> 01:03:00,844
We opened a barbershop next door,
where we give haircuts.

1440
01:03:01,611 --> 01:03:03,880
- How are you, sir?
- Hello, sir.

1441
01:03:03,947 --> 01:03:06,783
We opened a barbershop behind you

1442
01:03:06,850 --> 01:03:08,385
- and we came to say hi.
- Did you?

1443
01:03:08,451 --> 01:03:10,086
- Hello.
- Hello.

1444
01:03:10,987 --> 01:03:12,656
- We opened a barbershop.
- Yes.

1445
01:03:15,792 --> 01:03:18,595
- Do you give doggy cuts?
- Dog grooming is pretty hard.

1446
01:03:19,129 --> 01:03:20,764
I can trim the nails, though.

1447
01:03:21,631 --> 01:03:22,699
If you're free...

1448
01:03:22,766 --> 01:03:23,800
Ma'am.

1449
01:03:23,867 --> 01:03:25,268
- Hello.
- Hello.

1450
01:03:25,335 --> 01:03:26,569
Ma'am.

1451
01:03:27,003 --> 01:03:28,338
We met earlier, didn't we?

1452
01:03:28,405 --> 01:03:29,839
We have a gift for you.

1453
01:03:29,906 --> 01:03:32,142
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

1454
01:03:32,208 --> 01:03:34,144
THEY COULD ALMOST MEMORIZE THE AREA

1455
01:03:34,210 --> 01:03:35,378
- By the way,
- Yes.

1456
01:03:35,445 --> 01:03:37,414
what if the people we met today...

1457
01:03:37,480 --> 01:03:39,282
- All show up tomorrow?
- Yes.

1458
01:03:39,883 --> 01:03:40,884
You think so?

1459
01:03:41,051 --> 01:03:44,521
I'm starting to get scared
of cutting their hair.

1460
01:03:44,587 --> 01:03:46,523
- You're afraid?
- What if they don't like it?

1461
01:03:46,589 --> 01:03:47,924
FEELING EXTRA TENSE
AFTER MEETING THE LOCALS

1462
01:03:47,991 --> 01:03:50,593
- No way.
- They'll like it.

1463
01:03:51,661 --> 01:03:56,900
THEY HEAD HOME
UNDER ENDURING THE PRESSURE

1464
01:03:56,966 --> 01:03:59,269
- This is it.
- It's a really nice house.

1465
01:03:59,336 --> 01:04:00,670
Wow, what is this?

1466
01:04:01,004 --> 01:04:02,672
The front window is huge.

1467
01:04:07,077 --> 01:04:10,246
THEY HAD PROMOTED THE BUSINESS
IN THE EXTREME COLD

1468
01:04:10,313 --> 01:04:11,448
It's toasty warm.

1469
01:04:13,350 --> 01:04:14,751
What a nice place.

1470
01:04:14,818 --> 01:04:15,819
We're home.

1471
01:04:16,553 --> 01:04:17,554
Let's relax.

1472
01:04:18,121 --> 01:04:19,289
Don't you feel hungry?

1473
01:04:21,024 --> 01:04:24,127
FORGET COOKING,
DINNER IS BIBIMMYEON AND FRIED RICE

1474
01:04:29,432 --> 01:04:33,203
THE TRIO USED TO TALK ENDLESSLY

1475
01:04:33,837 --> 01:04:36,306
NOW THEY EAT IN SILENCE
DEEP IN THOUGHT

1476
01:04:36,373 --> 01:04:37,907
We start for real tomorrow.

1477
01:04:38,408 --> 01:04:39,642
Will we do well tomorrow?

1478
01:04:42,545 --> 01:04:44,514
- I'm worried it'll be crowded.
- Me too.

1479
01:04:45,148 --> 01:04:47,717
THEY FEEL WEIGHED DOWN

1480
01:04:47,784 --> 01:04:49,085
I feel nervous.

1481
01:04:50,286 --> 01:04:52,155
I feel tense, too.

1482
01:04:54,691 --> 01:04:57,994
Is it because there are
various hairstyles for women?

1483
01:04:58,495 --> 01:05:00,397
Well...

1484
01:05:00,463 --> 01:05:02,399
Do you find it easier
to cut a woman's hair?

1485
01:05:03,600 --> 01:05:05,902
It's easier to cut a man's hair

1486
01:05:05,969 --> 01:05:08,438
but recently, I'd focused on learning
how to cut women's hair.

1487
01:05:08,505 --> 01:05:10,507
I'm more used to handling

1488
01:05:11,107 --> 01:05:13,076
- longer hair.
- I guess.

1489
01:05:17,147 --> 01:05:20,350
EVERYTHING HE HAD ONLY IMAGINED

1490
01:05:20,417 --> 01:05:23,286
IS BECOMING A REALITY

1491
01:05:24,020 --> 01:05:25,455
HE TRIES

1492
01:05:25,522 --> 01:05:30,827
TO CALM HIS THOUGHTS
BY WASHING THE DISHES

1493
01:05:32,829 --> 01:05:34,864
DONG-YEON THE PHOTOGRAPHER DROPS BY

1494
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:36,800
POSING

1495
01:05:37,467 --> 01:05:38,968
BO GUM AS AN IDEAL HUSBAND

1496
01:05:39,402 --> 01:05:40,670
A BRIEF LAUGH THANKS TO DONG-YEON

1497
01:05:40,737 --> 01:05:41,938
- Me as a husband?
- Yes.

1498
01:05:42,639 --> 01:05:45,608
A HUSBAND THAT EXISTS
ONLY IN OUR WILDEST DREAMS

1499
01:05:45,675 --> 01:05:47,877
DID YOU CALL ME, HONEY?

1500
01:05:48,511 --> 01:05:51,381
A PHOTO OF SANG-YI AS A HUSBAND

1501
01:05:54,017 --> 01:05:56,820
NOW THIS IS A REALISTIC HUSBAND

1502
01:05:57,520 --> 01:06:01,424
HE'D BEEN ON EDGE WELCOMING CUSTOMERS
ALL DAY AND HE FELL ASLEEP

1503
01:06:02,392 --> 01:06:04,394
GIGGLING

1504
01:06:04,461 --> 01:06:07,630
A TYPICAL BREADWINNER IN ACTION

1505
01:06:08,798 --> 01:06:10,300
EYES SNAPPING OPEN

1506
01:06:10,366 --> 01:06:12,802
COUGHING

1507
01:06:13,670 --> 01:06:17,540
DAD'S AWAKE

1508
01:06:18,041 --> 01:06:19,542
OOPS

1509
01:06:19,609 --> 01:06:20,743
I fell asleep.

1510
01:06:21,144 --> 01:06:24,948
- Yes, did you sleep well?
- Yes, I was exhausted.

1511
01:06:25,281 --> 01:06:26,416
I'm sure you were.

1512
01:06:27,517 --> 01:06:30,186
I think cutting hair tomorrow
will take quite a while

1513
01:06:30,253 --> 01:06:31,254
since it's my first customer.

1514
01:06:32,155 --> 01:06:34,424
Our first business day will go well.

1515
01:06:34,491 --> 01:06:35,558
Let's do our best.

1516
01:06:35,625 --> 01:06:37,660
OUR FIRST DAY WILL GO WELL!

1517
01:06:38,628 --> 01:06:44,534
LATE AT NIGHT
WHEN EVERYONE IS IN BED

1518
01:06:48,605 --> 01:06:51,641
INSTEAD OF SLEEPING,
BO GUM COMES OUTSIDE

1519
01:06:52,675 --> 01:06:55,812
WHAT COULD BE THE MATTER
AT THIS HOUR?

1520
01:06:57,347 --> 01:07:01,017
HE SAUNTERS OFF ON HIS OWN

1521
01:07:01,584 --> 01:07:04,053
IT'S WAY AFTER MIDNIGHT

1522
01:07:04,654 --> 01:07:07,390
HIS WALK PICKS UP SPEED

1523
01:07:08,024 --> 01:07:10,727
BOUNCING

1524
01:07:11,928 --> 01:07:14,998
HE BRAVED THE COLD TO GET HERE

1525
01:07:18,868 --> 01:07:23,806
WHY IS HE AT THE EMPTY BARBERSHOP?

1526
01:07:25,708 --> 01:07:27,043
SNIPPING SOUNDS

1527
01:07:28,745 --> 01:07:31,881
BO GUM ASKED A CREW MEMBER FOR HELP
TO PRACTICE ONE LAST TIME

1528
01:07:32,515 --> 01:07:35,051
THE SOUND OF SCISSORS
FILLS THE DARK BARBERSHOP

1529
01:07:35,118 --> 01:07:36,185
The thing is...

1530
01:07:36,252 --> 01:07:40,256
This barbershop
operates under my name.

1531
01:07:41,491 --> 01:07:44,727
I came up with the awesome name,
The Village Barber

1532
01:07:44,794 --> 01:07:46,195
that has my name on it.

1533
01:07:47,263 --> 01:07:48,331
I wonder

1534
01:07:48,398 --> 01:07:52,035
if I'm prepared well enough
as the name suggests.

1535
01:07:52,101 --> 01:07:53,436
I'm looking back at my own self.

1536
01:07:53,503 --> 01:07:54,504
FEELING THE WEIGHT
OF RESPONSIBILITY

1537
01:07:55,238 --> 01:07:57,974
Will I be able to pull this off?

1538
01:08:03,179 --> 01:08:05,949
TO AVOID DISAPPOINTING ANYONE

1539
01:08:06,015 --> 01:08:08,051
HE PRACTICES CONTINUOUSLY

1540
01:08:08,117 --> 01:08:09,419
I must provide

1541
01:08:09,485 --> 01:08:11,487
the service
the customer wants exactly.

1542
01:08:12,488 --> 01:08:14,524
That's what makes my heart race.

1543
01:08:16,059 --> 01:08:17,594
I hope that

1544
01:08:17,994 --> 01:08:20,430
I can give the locals a magical time.

1545
01:08:23,032 --> 01:08:25,368
THE SLEEPLESS NIGHT PASSES

1546
01:08:26,669 --> 01:08:29,405
IT'S D-DAY AT LAST

1547
01:08:32,609 --> 01:08:38,247
SMOKE RISING FROM EVERY CHIMNEY

1548
01:08:39,816 --> 01:08:46,055
THE VILLAGE IS COATED IN AN ICY FROST

1549
01:08:46,723 --> 01:08:48,291
CURRENT TIME:
7:30 A.M.

1550
01:08:48,858 --> 01:08:52,495
SOMEONE'S ALARM GOES OFF

1551
01:08:53,563 --> 01:08:56,799
ANOTHER ALARM GOES OFF

1552
01:08:57,400 --> 01:09:01,270
A THIRD ALARM GOES OFF

1553
01:09:01,337 --> 01:09:04,507
THE HOUSE IS QUIET DESPITE THE ALARMS

1554
01:09:08,411 --> 01:09:11,748
SANG-YI IS UP

1555
01:09:12,281 --> 01:09:13,282
Man.

1556
01:09:14,751 --> 01:09:17,954
WHY IS IT MORNING ALREADY?

1557
01:09:20,523 --> 01:09:22,291
PLOPS DOWN

1558
01:09:28,064 --> 01:09:30,266
PUFFY FACE

1559
01:09:30,333 --> 01:09:33,069
Did I overwork myself yesterday?

1560
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:36,639
HERE'S SOMEONE WHO WORKED HARDER

1561
01:09:36,706 --> 01:09:37,707
- What's that?
- Hey.

1562
01:09:39,308 --> 01:09:40,843
- What?
- Are we both awake?

1563
01:09:40,910 --> 01:09:42,011
STARTLED

1564
01:09:42,812 --> 01:09:44,514
The floor is hot.

1565
01:09:44,981 --> 01:09:47,784
- Wasn't it too hot last night?
- No, it wasn't too hot.

1566
01:09:48,451 --> 01:09:50,586
I think I chose the wrong room.

1567
01:09:51,320 --> 01:09:53,790
- You got the long room?
- "Long..."

1568
01:09:53,856 --> 01:09:55,158
The "wrong" room.

1569
01:09:55,925 --> 01:09:57,326
GIGGLING

1570
01:09:57,393 --> 01:09:59,829
It got so hot
that I slept in my underwear.

1571
01:10:00,897 --> 01:10:02,165
You must've felt really hot.

1572
01:10:02,231 --> 01:10:05,401
That room got so hot
like a midsummer day.

1573
01:10:05,468 --> 01:10:06,869
THE EXTREME HEAT SOFTENED THEM UP

1574
01:10:09,272 --> 01:10:10,306
Your hair...

1575
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:12,341
It's a fistful.

1576
01:10:16,345 --> 01:10:18,214
- Gosh.
- You're like a Dragon Ball figure.

1577
01:10:20,083 --> 01:10:21,784
What time
did you get back last night?

1578
01:10:21,851 --> 01:10:22,919
Did you get back late?

1579
01:10:23,386 --> 01:10:26,022
Last night, I did one haircut.

1580
01:10:26,923 --> 01:10:28,524
Then a blow dry and a dye.

1581
01:10:29,158 --> 01:10:30,893
AMAZING

1582
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:34,030
It's cold today, right?

1583
01:10:34,731 --> 01:10:35,965
It's minus 10 degrees Celsius.

1584
01:10:37,300 --> 01:10:38,367
Feel it.

1585
01:10:39,268 --> 01:10:40,703
SURPRISED

1586
01:10:43,473 --> 01:10:45,942
FREEZING COLD

1587
01:10:46,743 --> 01:10:48,111
Let's not go outside today.

1588
01:10:48,177 --> 01:10:49,879
Let's stay inside the barbershop.

1589
01:10:52,515 --> 01:10:53,750
Good morning, everyone.

1590
01:10:53,816 --> 01:10:54,817
YOUNGSTER DONG-YEON'S READY, TOO

1591
01:10:55,585 --> 01:10:56,586
I turned off all the lights.

1592
01:10:59,222 --> 01:11:00,389
Watch your head.

1593
01:11:01,791 --> 01:11:02,792
THE THREE HEAD TO WORK TOGETHER

1594
01:11:02,859 --> 01:11:03,860
Let's go do business.

1595
01:11:05,461 --> 01:11:08,631
A NERVOUS BUT EXCITING
FIRST DAY OF WORK

1596
01:11:09,465 --> 01:11:10,466
A COFFEE POT TO SERVE THE CUSTOMERS

1597
01:11:10,533 --> 01:11:13,569
SLIPPERS TO WEAR INDOORS

1598
01:11:13,636 --> 01:11:15,204
The morning air makes me

1599
01:11:15,705 --> 01:11:17,573
- feel like I'm in Switzerland.
- Switzerland?

1600
01:11:18,407 --> 01:11:20,676
- I don't know. I've never been.
- Me neither.

1601
01:11:24,614 --> 01:11:27,083
- Hello and welcome.
- Hello.

1602
01:11:27,150 --> 01:11:29,051
THEY ARRIVE 1 HOUR BEFORE OPENING
AT 8 A.M.

1603
01:11:29,118 --> 01:11:31,888
- Shall we do a group cheer?
- Yes, let's do that.

1604
01:11:35,324 --> 01:11:37,593
- This is really...
- It's for real now.

1605
01:11:37,660 --> 01:11:39,428
Let's do well
without anyone getting hurt.

1606
01:11:39,495 --> 01:11:41,931
Don't get hurt
and let there be no bloodshed.

1607
01:11:41,998 --> 01:11:44,634
- One, two, three, let's go.
- Let's go.

1608
01:11:45,334 --> 01:11:46,469
First of all...

1609
01:11:47,003 --> 01:11:49,005
- Let's open for business.
- The light.

1610
01:11:49,071 --> 01:11:50,673
- The spinning light.
- Get it spinning.

1611
01:11:51,674 --> 01:11:53,209
I'm nervous.

1612
01:11:53,709 --> 01:11:54,811
Hold on.

1613
01:11:55,578 --> 01:11:56,813
Let's remember this moment.

1614
01:11:57,880 --> 01:11:59,215
This moment right now?

1615
01:11:59,282 --> 01:12:01,617
This hour. This moment in time.

1616
01:12:07,690 --> 01:12:10,193
- One, two, three.
- Turn it on.

1617
01:12:11,561 --> 01:12:12,862
It's on.

1618
01:12:12,929 --> 01:12:14,030
It's spinning.

1619
01:12:14,096 --> 01:12:16,365
The blood vessels
and bandages have started to spin.

1620
01:12:18,201 --> 01:12:19,669
Thanks, Dong-yeon.

1621
01:12:20,203 --> 01:12:22,238
GETTING READY TO OPEN!

1622
01:12:23,639 --> 01:12:25,775
PUTTING ON APRONS NEATLY

1623
01:12:26,275 --> 01:12:29,445
FOLDING GAUZE CLOTHS FOR MANICURES

1624
01:12:34,417 --> 01:12:38,688
SANG-YI PUTS THE TOOLS
IN THE STERILIZER

1625
01:12:50,266 --> 01:12:51,334
What time is it?

1626
01:12:51,400 --> 01:12:52,401
It's 8:55 a.m.

1627
01:12:52,468 --> 01:12:53,803
- Oh, my gosh.
- Hey, it's almost time.

1628
01:12:54,270 --> 01:12:56,038
- Let's go. Let's get ready.
- We've got five minutes left.

1629
01:12:56,105 --> 01:12:57,673
- Five minutes to go.
- What do I do?

1630
01:12:57,740 --> 01:12:58,741
What do I have to do?

1631
01:12:59,375 --> 01:13:00,476
Make the welcome drinks?

1632
01:13:01,244 --> 01:13:02,578
You serve the welcome drinks.

1633
01:13:02,645 --> 01:13:04,146
We'll greet the customers.

1634
01:13:04,714 --> 01:13:05,948
Should we stand over here?

1635
01:13:06,949 --> 01:13:09,318
STAND RIGHT HERE?

1636
01:13:09,919 --> 01:13:12,154
We're three minutes away.
Where's my tea?

1637
01:13:12,221 --> 01:13:13,389
It's over here.

1638
01:13:13,890 --> 01:13:15,658
Does your body and mind need calming?

1639
01:13:17,026 --> 01:13:19,762
HE NEEDS TO PREPARE HIMSELF
BEFORE THE OPENING

1640
01:13:22,531 --> 01:13:24,533
All my equipment is ready.

1641
01:13:25,234 --> 01:13:28,304
JUST 3 MINUTES TO OPENING!

1642
01:13:38,547 --> 01:13:41,117
I'm nervous that someone might come.

1643
01:13:46,555 --> 01:13:47,890
It's nine o'clock.

1644
01:13:52,662 --> 01:13:54,163
- It's 9?
- Yes.

1645
01:14:05,041 --> 01:14:08,144
SILENCE

1646
01:14:08,577 --> 01:14:11,280
NO ONE TO THE LEFT

1647
01:14:12,315 --> 01:14:15,017
AN EMPTY STREET TO THE RIGHT

1648
01:14:16,385 --> 01:14:18,120
LOOKING DEJECTED FROM BEHIND

1649
01:14:19,322 --> 01:14:21,424
There's no one in the street.

1650
01:14:21,958 --> 01:14:24,460
- Is it too early in the morning?
- Is it too early?

1651
01:14:24,527 --> 01:14:26,429
I guess they'll come
after breakfast, right?

1652
01:14:26,495 --> 01:14:27,496
Yes, you're right.

1653
01:14:30,066 --> 01:14:31,901
When we opened at 9 a.m.

1654
01:14:31,968 --> 01:14:35,237
I thought
we'd be swamped by a massive crowd.

1655
01:14:36,439 --> 01:14:37,707
I thought that at 9 sharp...

1656
01:14:38,474 --> 01:14:41,143
- The customers...
- There's none.

1657
01:14:41,210 --> 01:14:42,511
NO ONE WAITED FOR US TO OPEN

1658
01:14:44,180 --> 01:14:48,651
Did you think or hope some customers
would line up before you opened?

1659
01:14:48,718 --> 01:14:52,655
No. I didn't expect
or hope for that at all.

1660
01:14:53,489 --> 01:14:56,359
THE LOOK OF A MAN
WHO HAD NO EXPECTATIONS

1661
01:14:57,426 --> 01:15:01,364
For someone who had no expectations,
BO GUM keeps gazing out the window.

1662
01:15:05,301 --> 01:15:07,737
EVEN AS HE PUTS THINGS AWAY

1663
01:15:07,803 --> 01:15:09,905
HE LOOKS OUTSIDE

1664
01:15:16,979 --> 01:15:21,951
EVEN AS HE CLEANS UP,
HE LOOKS OUTSIDE

1665
01:15:23,252 --> 01:15:25,021
I hear a motorbike.

1666
01:15:32,561 --> 01:15:35,131
A MOTORBIKE GOING BY

1667
01:15:39,602 --> 01:15:41,303
NOT A CUSTOMER

1668
01:15:47,910 --> 01:15:49,211
My imagination

1669
01:15:49,278 --> 01:15:50,713
was far from reality.

1670
01:15:51,447 --> 01:15:52,448
I thought

1671
01:15:52,515 --> 01:15:54,283
- as soon as we opened,
- Me too.

1672
01:15:54,350 --> 01:15:56,685
people would flock to the door and
ask, "Is this The Village Barber?"

1673
01:15:58,020 --> 01:15:59,255
"I'm here to get my hair done."

1674
01:15:59,321 --> 01:16:01,123
They'd say,
"I've been waiting for hours."

1675
01:16:01,724 --> 01:16:03,926
BOSS PARK GRINS FROM EAR TO EAR

1676
01:16:03,993 --> 01:16:09,865
BUT IN REALITY

1677
01:16:09,932 --> 01:16:14,170
0 PEOPLE WAITING IN LINE

1678
01:16:14,236 --> 01:16:16,305
Are they not coming out
because it's too cold?

1679
01:16:16,372 --> 01:16:19,175
- That could be it.
- It's minus 10 degrees.

1680
01:16:20,109 --> 01:16:22,912
IS IT USUALLY LIKE THIS?

1681
01:16:23,446 --> 01:16:26,048
KEEPS GLANCING

1682
01:16:26,115 --> 01:16:28,284
- I can't stop looking over there.
- Me too.

1683
01:16:29,118 --> 01:16:30,753
I hope someone comes soon.

1684
01:16:30,820 --> 01:16:33,856
EARNESTLY HOPING FOR SOMEONE TO COME

1685
01:16:35,257 --> 01:16:37,593
I WISH TO CLING TO ANYONE

1686
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:39,662
Should we do another broadcast?

1687
01:16:40,696 --> 01:16:42,865
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

1688
01:16:47,970 --> 01:16:50,439
THEY'RE ALL TOO BUSY TO NOTICE

1689
01:16:51,807 --> 01:16:53,142
Hey, a grandma is coming.

1690
01:16:53,209 --> 01:16:54,443
- What?
- A grandma's coming.

1691
01:16:54,510 --> 01:16:55,511
She's here? Hang on.

1692
01:17:00,449 --> 01:17:01,750
IN A RUSH

1693
01:17:02,451 --> 01:17:03,752
A BIG RUSH

1694
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:07,923
- She's walking on by.
- She is?

1695
01:17:09,258 --> 01:17:11,827
JUST PASSING BY

1696
01:17:12,828 --> 01:17:14,296
She walked on by?

1697
01:17:14,797 --> 01:17:16,599
Good morning, ma'am.

1698
01:17:16,665 --> 01:17:18,934
- Hello.
- Hello, where are you off to?

1699
01:17:19,368 --> 01:17:20,536
Oh, you're visiting Ms. Kim Jeong-ja.

1700
01:17:21,770 --> 01:17:23,839
- Did you have breakfast?
- We will now.

1701
01:17:23,906 --> 01:17:25,708
- Did you eat?
- I will now.

1702
01:17:25,774 --> 01:17:27,743
- Okay.
- Come see us later.

1703
01:17:27,810 --> 01:17:28,811
Okay.

1704
01:17:33,482 --> 01:17:35,317
- My heart raced a bit.
- I guess

1705
01:17:35,384 --> 01:17:37,419
- she had somewhere to go.
- Yes. Breakfast...

1706
01:17:37,486 --> 01:17:40,856
I guess they get together
to have breakfast.

1707
01:17:43,526 --> 01:17:45,094
- Come and sit down.
- Me too.

1708
01:17:45,161 --> 01:17:47,963
SANG-YI SUDDENLY SUMMONS BO GUM

1709
01:17:49,899 --> 01:17:52,101
- I'll color just one little finger.
- Okay.

1710
01:17:52,535 --> 01:17:55,171
I'll become a fancy barbershop owner.

1711
01:17:55,905 --> 01:17:56,906
GLANCING

1712
01:17:57,406 --> 01:17:58,774
THE TWO GLANCE OUT THE WINDOW
LIKE MEERKATS

1713
01:17:58,841 --> 01:17:59,975
Your nails are so well-kept.

1714
01:18:03,746 --> 01:18:06,949
- It's the one with iron particles.
- Do you see the iron powder?

1715
01:18:09,218 --> 01:18:10,686
Hang on. After putting it on...

1716
01:18:11,654 --> 01:18:14,990
THE IRON PARTICLES FOLLOW THE MAGNET

1717
01:18:15,691 --> 01:18:18,928
- It's pretty with a gradient look.
- Right?

1718
01:18:20,095 --> 01:18:22,298
NOW TO HARDEN THE GEL WITH A LAMP

1719
01:18:22,364 --> 01:18:24,066
NO CUSTOMERS YET?

1720
01:18:24,133 --> 01:18:25,301
- It's hot.
- Was it hot?

1721
01:18:25,367 --> 01:18:26,969
STARTLED

1722
01:18:27,469 --> 01:18:28,470
- It's hot.
- Be careful.

1723
01:18:29,071 --> 01:18:31,640
It happens.

1724
01:18:31,707 --> 01:18:34,643
But using this lamp on the elderly...

1725
01:18:35,377 --> 01:18:36,912
I don't think
I should use gel on them.

1726
01:18:37,546 --> 01:18:38,948
This usually gets hot.

1727
01:18:39,415 --> 01:18:41,650
- It's a chemical effect.
- It was crazy hot.

1728
01:18:41,717 --> 01:18:43,252
- Is it okay now?
- Yes.

1729
01:18:43,319 --> 01:18:45,421
It was a good experience.
I'm glad we got to practice.

1730
01:18:45,487 --> 01:18:46,655
It could've been a disaster.

1731
01:18:47,122 --> 01:18:48,924
- That was a disaster averted.
- Wait, watch out.

1732
01:18:50,993 --> 01:18:52,027
It was crazy hot.

1733
01:18:54,129 --> 01:18:55,364
- There are these colors.
- Hey.

1734
01:18:55,431 --> 01:18:56,465
Purple would look pretty.

1735
01:18:56,532 --> 01:18:57,533
Yes, let's try purple.

1736
01:18:58,400 --> 01:18:59,635
- It won't be hot this time.
- Okay.

1737
01:18:59,702 --> 01:19:01,570
Look at the sample colors here.

1738
01:19:01,637 --> 01:19:03,038
- I see.
- There are more over there.

1739
01:19:03,472 --> 01:19:04,607
I think purple would be pretty.

1740
01:19:04,673 --> 01:19:07,109
Is this what you did on my finger?
Hey, it's pretty.

1741
01:19:07,176 --> 01:19:08,177
GOT DISTRACTED

1742
01:19:10,946 --> 01:19:12,815
Why is it so cold today?

1743
01:19:12,881 --> 01:19:14,450
- This won't be hot.
- Hey, someone's here.

1744
01:19:15,985 --> 01:19:18,153
- Hey, someone's here. Look!
- Oh, my.

1745
01:19:18,220 --> 01:19:19,288
BO GUM.

1746
01:19:19,355 --> 01:19:21,190
- Someone's coming.
- Oh, my.

1747
01:19:28,330 --> 01:19:29,465
- Welcome.
- Ma'am.

1748
01:19:30,165 --> 01:19:32,368
- Hey, someone's here. Look!
- Oh, my.

1749
01:19:32,434 --> 01:19:33,435
SOMEONE'S COMING

1750
01:19:34,903 --> 01:19:37,940
- Why is it so cold today?
- It's really cold.

1751
01:19:38,240 --> 01:19:40,509
IS IT THE FIRST CUSTOMER
THEY WERE WAITING FOR?

1752
01:19:40,576 --> 01:19:43,212
EXCLAIMING

1753
01:19:46,048 --> 01:19:48,284
- Ma'am.
- Hello.

1754
01:19:48,350 --> 01:19:50,753
- Welcome.
- What brings you...

1755
01:19:51,787 --> 01:19:53,989
- Ma'am.
- Hello.

1756
01:19:54,056 --> 01:19:56,492
THE NEXT-DOOR NEIGHBOR
WHO VISITED YESTERDAY

1757
01:19:56,558 --> 01:19:58,527
- Welcome.
- What brings you...

1758
01:19:58,961 --> 01:20:00,929
- They came in together.
- Miss Jeong-ja.

1759
01:20:01,463 --> 01:20:05,367
My daughter-in-law
bought some curly dried laver.

1760
01:20:05,434 --> 01:20:06,669
I cooked it on an open flame.

1761
01:20:06,735 --> 01:20:08,671
- I see.
- I thought of you.

1762
01:20:08,737 --> 01:20:10,539
- I hope you enjoy it.
- Thank you.

1763
01:20:11,206 --> 01:20:12,875
- It's coated in perilla oil.
- Oh, dear.

1764
01:20:12,941 --> 01:20:14,943
- I had nothing else to bring.
- That's fine.

1765
01:20:15,010 --> 01:20:16,645
- The fact that you're here...
- You gave us kimchi...

1766
01:20:16,712 --> 01:20:18,547
You gave us kimchi,
which we thoroughly enjoyed.

1767
01:20:18,614 --> 01:20:20,516
- That's right.
- Seriously...

1768
01:20:20,582 --> 01:20:23,018
You're the first customers
since our official opening.

1769
01:20:23,085 --> 01:20:25,521
- Oh, is that so?
- Thank you for coming.

1770
01:20:26,288 --> 01:20:28,257
- Thank you.
- Thanks for having us.

1771
01:20:28,324 --> 01:20:31,093
- Will you make us a cup of coffee?
- Would you like some coffee?

1772
01:20:31,160 --> 01:20:32,661
- That sweet kind.
- The instant coffee mix.

1773
01:20:32,728 --> 01:20:33,762
- The sweet kind.
- Yes.

1774
01:20:33,829 --> 01:20:36,498
- The one in the easy-rip packet.
- The packaged kind.

1775
01:20:36,565 --> 01:20:39,902
- Sweet coffee. I'll make it hot.
- Yes, with extra water.

1776
01:20:40,469 --> 01:20:42,938
SNAPPING THE END OFF A PACKET

1777
01:20:44,907 --> 01:20:47,609
CIRCULAR MOTION

1778
01:20:47,676 --> 01:20:50,379
TREATING IT LIKE IT'S DRIP COFFEE

1779
01:20:50,779 --> 01:20:52,981
What's your name, madam?

1780
01:20:53,048 --> 01:20:55,718
- It's Ou Yun-ok. Why do you ask?
- Ou.

1781
01:20:56,118 --> 01:20:58,020
- Ms. Yun-ok.
- Ou Yun-ok.

1782
01:20:58,487 --> 01:21:00,889
- Do you need to get your hair done?
- Leave it.

1783
01:21:01,657 --> 01:21:02,658
Leave it.

1784
01:21:02,725 --> 01:21:05,861
DIDN'T YOU COME
TO GET YOUR HAIR DONE?

1785
01:21:05,928 --> 01:21:06,962
I'm busy.

1786
01:21:07,029 --> 01:21:09,798
I came to watch
because she wanted her hair done.

1787
01:21:10,532 --> 01:21:12,167
You look beautiful today.

1788
01:21:12,234 --> 01:21:14,336
- You're even wearing lipstick.
- Of course.

1789
01:21:14,937 --> 01:21:15,938
WHISPERING

1790
01:21:16,538 --> 01:21:17,940
THE CAMERA'S FILMING US

1791
01:21:20,642 --> 01:21:21,643
She'll be on TV.

1792
01:21:22,644 --> 01:21:24,146
SHE'S ADORABLE

1793
01:21:24,580 --> 01:21:26,882
STIRRING

1794
01:21:30,953 --> 01:21:32,388
- Here you go.
- Oh, thank you.

1795
01:21:32,454 --> 01:21:33,722
- I'll enjoy it.
- Please do.

1796
01:21:33,789 --> 01:21:36,525
Thanks a lot. It smells lovely.

1797
01:21:38,594 --> 01:21:40,062
Gosh, that tastes nice.

1798
01:21:41,430 --> 01:21:43,499
- You made a lovely cup.
- Thank you.

1799
01:21:45,667 --> 01:21:47,202
It tastes best
when someone else makes it.

1800
01:21:48,070 --> 01:21:51,540
- We opened at 9 a.m. today.
- I see.

1801
01:21:51,607 --> 01:21:54,109
We worried we weren't
going to have any customers.

1802
01:21:54,176 --> 01:21:55,811
Why say that? You'll have customers.

1803
01:21:55,878 --> 01:21:58,414
They'll slowly start to come by
to hang out.

1804
01:21:58,714 --> 01:22:00,282
- Wouldn't they?
- What?

1805
01:22:00,349 --> 01:22:02,117
I don't know
where Mi-yeong's family went.

1806
01:22:02,384 --> 01:22:04,052
Where'd she go? To Seoul, maybe.

1807
01:22:04,119 --> 01:22:06,188
No, she'd tell me if she was
going to Seoul, but she didn't.

1808
01:22:06,255 --> 01:22:07,289
To Seoul, maybe.

1809
01:22:07,356 --> 01:22:09,291
No, she'd tell me if she was
going to Seoul, but she didn't.

1810
01:22:09,358 --> 01:22:11,226
- Who do you mean?
- She didn't mention Seoul.

1811
01:22:12,795 --> 01:22:13,829
One of our neighbors.

1812
01:22:13,896 --> 01:22:16,131
- One of our neighbors.
- Another friend?

1813
01:22:16,865 --> 01:22:18,100
She didn't go to Seoul.

1814
01:22:18,167 --> 01:22:21,370
PURE, UNFILTERED BANTER AT ITS FINEST

1815
01:22:21,437 --> 01:22:25,174
My San-suk's daughter
is getting married in February.

1816
01:22:25,240 --> 01:22:26,442
She'll bring her fiancé around.

1817
01:22:26,508 --> 01:22:28,677
- You must look pretty.
- They're coming to see me.

1818
01:22:28,744 --> 01:22:30,446
Do you want your hair done, then?

1819
01:22:30,512 --> 01:22:33,215
- It would be nice to look nice.
- Of course.

1820
01:22:33,282 --> 01:22:36,552
What hairstyle would you like,
Ms. Jeong-ja?

1821
01:22:36,618 --> 01:22:38,220
- Shall I color your hair?
- Yes.

1822
01:22:38,287 --> 01:22:40,022
- Some color.
- The roots over here.

1823
01:22:41,023 --> 01:22:43,659
- You don't have to color much.
- Okay.

1824
01:22:44,993 --> 01:22:45,994
Make her look good.

1825
01:22:46,061 --> 01:22:47,062
BO GUM'S FIRST JOB
IS DYEING GRAY HAIR

1826
01:22:50,466 --> 01:22:53,602
HE GETS A ROBE

1827
01:22:53,669 --> 01:22:55,003
Wear this on top.

1828
01:22:59,441 --> 01:23:00,909
Take a seat.

1829
01:23:00,976 --> 01:23:03,045
BO GUM SHOWS HER TO HER SEAT

1830
01:23:03,111 --> 01:23:05,614
I painted your nails yesterday.

1831
01:23:06,081 --> 01:23:07,983
You're our number one
and best customer.

1832
01:23:08,517 --> 01:23:10,819
- You're a VIP.
- That's right.

1833
01:23:11,220 --> 01:23:14,490
- Ms. Jeong-ja.
- Yes. I'll dye your hair first.

1834
01:23:15,891 --> 01:23:17,493
Can you trim it before dyeing it?

1835
01:23:17,559 --> 01:23:19,328
- Shall I trim it a bit?
- Yes.

1836
01:23:19,394 --> 01:23:20,529
COLORING GRAYING HAIRS

1837
01:23:20,596 --> 01:23:22,798
SUDDEN ADDITION OF A TRIM

1838
01:23:22,865 --> 01:23:26,702
- When will we see you again?
- We'll visit often.

1839
01:23:26,768 --> 01:23:28,904
BO GUM PUTS ON HIS TOOL BELT
TO TRIM HER HAIR

1840
01:23:30,339 --> 01:23:32,508
IT'S TIME TO GIVE HIS FIRST HAIRCUT

1841
01:23:32,574 --> 01:23:34,710
- The peach flowers are pretty.
- You're my first customer.

1842
01:23:39,915 --> 01:23:41,950
- Because I'll be dyeing your hair,
- Yes.

1843
01:23:42,017 --> 01:23:44,253
- I won't wash your hair for now.
- Okay.

1844
01:23:46,021 --> 01:23:49,091
When my granddaughter visits
with her fiancé

1845
01:23:49,157 --> 01:23:52,094
I want to give the impression

1846
01:23:52,160 --> 01:23:56,131
that his future mother-in-law's mom
has a nice haircut.

1847
01:23:56,198 --> 01:23:58,934
Okay. I'll try to make you look nice.

1848
01:24:01,069 --> 01:24:04,106
THE COMB AND SCISSORS ARE OUT

1849
01:24:09,611 --> 01:24:11,346
I won't cut off too much.

1850
01:24:11,413 --> 01:24:14,483
- Shall I give you a trim?
- Yes, do that.

1851
01:24:15,484 --> 01:24:16,685
GULP

1852
01:24:16,985 --> 01:24:18,654
GULP

1853
01:24:19,321 --> 01:24:24,026
IT'S A FIRST FOR BOTH
THE ROOKIE BARBER AND HIS CUSTOMER

1854
01:24:24,092 --> 01:24:26,528
It was my first day.

1855
01:24:26,595 --> 01:24:29,264
I felt nervous and pressured.

1856
01:24:29,665 --> 01:24:31,166
It weighed on me.

1857
01:24:32,668 --> 01:24:35,337
HE PRACTICED A LONG TIME
FOR THIS MOMENT

1858
01:24:35,938 --> 01:24:39,474
To do what the customer wants.

1859
01:24:39,541 --> 01:24:44,980
I'll remember what I learned
and make them look the best I can.

1860
01:24:45,480 --> 01:24:48,951
I hope they reciprocate my touch.

1861
01:24:51,053 --> 01:24:52,588
This is making me feel weird.

1862
01:24:53,522 --> 01:24:55,857
I feel more solemn now that's up.

1863
01:24:55,924 --> 01:24:57,559
Right? I feel weird, too.

1864
01:24:58,694 --> 01:25:01,363
Once I make a cut,
there's no going back.

1865
01:25:01,763 --> 01:25:03,031
What if they don't like it?

1866
01:25:03,632 --> 01:25:05,033
Will we do well tomorrow?

1867
01:25:05,567 --> 01:25:06,635
I'm worried.

1868
01:25:07,569 --> 01:25:09,271
Let's do well
without anyone getting hurt.

1869
01:25:09,338 --> 01:25:11,907
Don't get hurt
and let there be no bloodshed.

1870
01:25:11,974 --> 01:25:15,010
- One, two, three, let's go.
- Let's go.

1871
01:25:37,466 --> 01:25:43,138
BO GUM PUTS HIS SCISSORS TO WORK
FOR THE FIRST TIME

1872
01:25:49,778 --> 01:25:51,079
He started cutting.

1873
01:25:52,581 --> 01:25:53,582
What is it?

1874
01:25:55,183 --> 01:25:57,986
It somehow feels strange
to see you cutting hair.

1875
01:26:00,622 --> 01:26:02,891
IT'S THE FIRST TIME EITHER OF THEM

1876
01:26:02,958 --> 01:26:06,128
HAVE SEEN BO GUM USE HIS SCISSORS

1877
01:26:16,304 --> 01:26:22,310
DESPITE ALL HIS PRACTICE,
PERMED HAIR IS HARD TO CUT STRAIGHT

1878
01:26:27,382 --> 01:26:29,184
BO GUM DROPS HIS COMB
OUT OF NERVOUSNESS

1879
01:26:29,251 --> 01:26:30,552
Sorry.

1880
01:26:32,487 --> 01:26:33,789
PRETENDING NOT TO NOTICE

1881
01:26:33,855 --> 01:26:35,090
Sorry.

1882
01:26:35,157 --> 01:26:38,360
IMMEDIATELY SWITCHING TO A CLEAN COMB

1883
01:26:40,162 --> 01:26:42,631
FOCUSED

1884
01:26:44,833 --> 01:26:46,635
WINCING

1885
01:26:51,907 --> 01:26:53,275
OOPS

1886
01:26:55,243 --> 01:26:59,347
BO GUM NIPPED HIS FINGER BY MISTAKE

1887
01:27:04,119 --> 01:27:07,456
SHE HASN'T NOTICED THE INJURY

1888
01:27:09,524 --> 01:27:11,593
BLOOD IS SEEPING OUT ALREADY!

1889
01:27:13,328 --> 01:27:15,063
Oh, dear.

1890
01:27:17,733 --> 01:27:18,734
Excuse me.

1891
01:27:18,800 --> 01:27:20,302
DASHING OFF

1892
01:27:25,107 --> 01:27:30,979
IS BO GUM FACING A CRISIS ON DAY 1?

1893
01:27:33,448 --> 01:27:36,218
- Welcome.
- This is The Village Barber.

1894
01:27:36,284 --> 01:27:37,919
- Shall I trim it a bit?
- Yes.

1895
01:27:38,653 --> 01:27:39,855
He cut his finger.

1896
01:27:40,355 --> 01:27:41,790
Wait a second...

1897
01:27:41,857 --> 01:27:43,125
Just hold on.

1898
01:27:43,191 --> 01:27:44,626
I came for a haircut.

1899
01:27:44,693 --> 01:27:46,261
THE WAIT HERE IS PRETTY LONG

1900
01:27:46,328 --> 01:27:47,429
I'm sorry.

1901
01:27:47,496 --> 01:27:49,131
- I'll start from this point.
- Okay.

1902
01:27:49,765 --> 01:27:51,867
Oh, my.
She doesn't have any ear covers on.

1903
01:27:52,334 --> 01:27:53,335
EXCUSE ME?

1904
01:27:53,401 --> 01:27:55,137
- Oh, my. The ear covers...
- Oh, dear.

1905
01:27:55,203 --> 01:27:56,638
You can smear it all over.

1906
01:27:56,705 --> 01:27:58,573
JUST SMEAR
THE HAIR DYE ON

1907
01:27:58,640 --> 01:28:01,176
Go ahead and just slap it on there.

1908
01:28:01,243 --> 01:28:03,145
- Right, so it doesn't go to waste.
- That's right.

1909
01:28:04,112 --> 01:28:05,213
DYEING THE FOREHEAD AS A BONUS

1910
01:28:05,814 --> 01:28:06,848
- Oh, my gosh.
- Oh, dear.

1911
01:28:06,915 --> 01:28:08,183
He's all soaked.

1912
01:28:08,250 --> 01:28:09,751
A SOAK FEST IN THE SHAMPOO ROOM

1913
01:28:09,818 --> 01:28:10,819
Oh, my.

1914
01:28:10,886 --> 01:28:13,088
- We're here to have a look.
- Oh, my.

1915
01:28:13,155 --> 01:28:14,356
What a hectic day.

1916
01:28:14,422 --> 01:28:15,824
- A nail art?
- Yes.

1917
01:28:15,891 --> 01:28:17,692
Who's next?

1918
01:28:17,759 --> 01:28:19,795
Two with custard filling
and two with red bean filling.

1919
01:28:19,861 --> 01:28:21,596
Gosh, it's so good.

1920
01:28:22,364 --> 01:28:23,965
What a pity. He must be exhausted.

1921
01:28:24,299 --> 01:28:25,600
How would you like your hair done?

1922
01:28:25,667 --> 01:28:27,235
Like Jang Won-young of IVE.

1923
01:28:28,236 --> 01:28:30,138
This is a popular hairstyle
these days, too.

1924
01:28:31,039 --> 01:28:32,607
She doesn't look too happy.

1925
01:28:32,674 --> 01:28:36,244
- You're just nervous. That's all.
- Right, I'm just nervous.

1926
01:28:36,311 --> 01:28:37,846
WILL THE VILLAGE BARBER
SURVIVE THEIR FIRST DAY?

1927
01:28:42,083 --> 01:28:43,351
THE VILLAGE BARBER

1928
01:28:50,959 --> 01:28:52,861
THE VILLAGE BARBER

1929
01:28:54,863 --> 01:28:56,865
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn, Hoyoung Yun,
and Jennifer Lim
